1
00:00:17,703 --> 00:00:20,803
(This is a record of the desperate survival story...)

2
00:00:21,743 --> 00:00:23,803
(of four siblings.)

3
00:00:27,443 --> 00:00:31,553
(Mangrove forest of the Philippines)

4
00:00:32,453 --> 00:00:33,553
It's no joke.

5
00:00:37,153 --> 00:00:38,953
It's a first to fail this miserably.

6
00:00:41,193 --> 00:00:42,493
Mother! Gosh.

7
00:00:43,963 --> 00:00:45,563
(Yum Jung Ah)

8
00:00:47,033 --> 00:00:50,202
(Park Jun Myun)

9
00:00:50,203 --> 00:00:51,433
I thought this was a vacation.

10
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:54,573
(Kim Jin Young)

11
00:00:55,673 --> 00:00:58,543
(Kim Hye Yoon)

12
00:00:59,243 --> 00:01:04,143
(There's light!)

13
00:01:04,613 --> 00:01:06,213
How is this a vacation?

14
00:01:06,313 --> 00:01:09,953
(They have fallen into the trap.)

15
00:01:11,053 --> 00:01:13,653
(February 2026, Seoul)

16
00:01:14,723 --> 00:01:17,723
(There are posters with an unfamiliar language...)

17
00:01:18,563 --> 00:01:20,933
(with exotic dishes.)

18
00:01:21,863 --> 00:01:23,632
- Hello. - Hello.

19
00:01:23,633 --> 00:01:26,033
(The sisters have gathered at a Southeast Asian restaurant.)

20
00:01:26,303 --> 00:01:28,573
(Looking around)

21
00:01:28,903 --> 00:01:29,973
What is this place?

22
00:01:30,103 --> 00:01:31,713
It must be a famous place.

23
00:01:31,913 --> 00:01:34,713
It feels like we're filming the opening scene of our show...

24
00:01:35,643 --> 00:01:37,082
- at the countryside. - Right.

25
00:01:37,083 --> 00:01:40,413
We met each other with Jin Young in November.

26
00:01:40,553 --> 00:01:43,033
It must be around 2 to 3 months since we met each other again.

27
00:01:43,383 --> 00:01:46,023
- Jung Ah lost weight, and so did I. - Right.

28
00:01:46,223 --> 00:01:48,593
- You lost a lot, didn't you? - Right. I lost around 10kg.

29
00:01:49,363 --> 00:01:52,193
It was tough for me with all of my performances.

30
00:01:52,463 --> 00:01:54,193
- You cut off late-night snacks. - Right.

31
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,163
I stopped eating after 8pm.

32
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:58,872
Did you eat a lot after 8pm before that?

33
00:01:58,873 --> 00:01:59,933
Right.

34
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:03,073
- I didn't eat that much. - Why did you gain so much, then?

35
00:02:03,573 --> 00:02:05,572
(It was out of pure curiosity from the thinker.)

36
00:02:05,573 --> 00:02:07,543
If you ask me such a straightforward question,

37
00:02:08,213 --> 00:02:09,412
it will make me feel embarrassed to answer.

38
00:02:09,413 --> 00:02:12,089
You look the prettiest right now out of all of the times we've met.

39
00:02:12,113 --> 00:02:14,583
(She just laughs as she feels shy.)

40
00:02:15,083 --> 00:02:16,152
That was why...

41
00:02:16,153 --> 00:02:17,423
- He's here! - Hey!

42
00:02:17,553 --> 00:02:18,793
Jin Young!

43
00:02:19,993 --> 00:02:21,913
- Jin Young is here. - Have you been doing well?

44
00:02:22,793 --> 00:02:23,892
I missed you so much.

45
00:02:23,893 --> 00:02:25,362
Jin Young! Have you been doing well?

46
00:02:25,363 --> 00:02:26,732
- Yes. I've been doing well. - Right.

47
00:02:26,733 --> 00:02:28,803
- I see you a lot on TV. - Me?

48
00:02:31,003 --> 00:02:32,432
You look even better now.

49
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:33,533
Really?

50
00:02:33,873 --> 00:02:35,973
(Feeling shy)

51
00:02:36,173 --> 00:02:37,542
What's with the glasses? Are they prescription glasses?

52
00:02:37,543 --> 00:02:38,643
- No. - No.

53
00:02:38,743 --> 00:02:39,872
There aren't even any lenses?

54
00:02:39,873 --> 00:02:42,013
- He wore them to look smart. - Right.

55
00:02:42,113 --> 00:02:43,543
As it's our first meeting together.

56
00:02:44,513 --> 00:02:46,483
It's been a while since I saw you two.

57
00:02:47,013 --> 00:02:49,583
(It's been 3 months since they've met each other separately.)

58
00:02:49,723 --> 00:02:51,099
You feel awkward right now, don't you?

59
00:02:51,123 --> 00:02:52,892
- No. I don't feel awkward. - No?

60
00:02:52,893 --> 00:02:56,023
We've been texting each other a lot as well.

61
00:02:56,723 --> 00:02:57,862
We said we wanted to go on a trip together.

62
00:02:57,863 --> 00:02:58,992
Right.

63
00:02:58,993 --> 00:03:00,792
I was a guest in Season Two,

64
00:03:00,793 --> 00:03:02,603
but I wanted to spend more time together.

65
00:03:02,703 --> 00:03:05,503
It's best to be with each other until the very end.

66
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:09,743
I mentioned that I wanted to go on another trip with everyone.

67
00:03:09,943 --> 00:03:11,773
I really wanted to make it happen.

68
00:03:12,113 --> 00:03:14,573
(The group chat of Fresh Off the Sea)

69
00:03:14,683 --> 00:03:15,683
(You're all doing well, right?)

70
00:03:15,684 --> 00:03:16,842
(I want to be on the show again after meeting all of you.)

71
00:03:16,843 --> 00:03:17,912
(You want to work again?)

72
00:03:17,913 --> 00:03:18,952
(It would be great to go on a trip together and have great food.)

73
00:03:18,953 --> 00:03:19,982
(That would be great.)

74
00:03:19,983 --> 00:03:21,012
(Let's make it happen!)

75
00:03:21,013 --> 00:03:22,582
(I would love to go, Jung Ah.)

76
00:03:22,583 --> 00:03:25,323
(The members all wanted to go on a trip together.)

77
00:03:25,523 --> 00:03:27,393
Did you get your work schedule sorted out?

78
00:03:27,853 --> 00:03:30,193
I will automatically come out if Jung Ah gives me a call.

79
00:03:30,763 --> 00:03:32,833
- I'm always ready. - Impressive.

80
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:34,033
I can always count on you.

81
00:03:34,034 --> 00:03:36,232
While being on Fresh Off the Sea,

82
00:03:36,233 --> 00:03:38,302
you all have suffered so much...

83
00:03:38,303 --> 00:03:40,373
during the summer season and the winter season.

84
00:03:40,673 --> 00:03:43,073
(Blazing summer)

85
00:03:43,173 --> 00:03:45,273
(Chilly winter)

86
00:03:45,443 --> 00:03:47,842
(In the field)

87
00:03:47,843 --> 00:03:50,042
(At the sea)

88
00:03:50,043 --> 00:03:52,212
(With desperation)

89
00:03:52,213 --> 00:03:54,682
(With pain)

90
00:03:54,683 --> 00:03:57,052
(The siblings have worked...)

91
00:03:57,053 --> 00:03:59,523
(with everything they've got.)

92
00:03:59,693 --> 00:04:01,762
You all will travel abroad to go on vacation.

93
00:04:01,763 --> 00:04:02,793
- Really? - Yes!

94
00:04:05,363 --> 00:04:06,593
Make some noise!

95
00:04:07,393 --> 00:04:09,433
- We won't be working? - We must be free from work.

96
00:04:09,463 --> 00:04:10,732
But... Really?

97
00:04:10,733 --> 00:04:12,873
- Think of it as a vacation. - Really?

98
00:04:13,103 --> 00:04:14,202
- All that hard work... - You should thank me.

99
00:04:14,203 --> 00:04:16,542
Is being rewarded like this.

100
00:04:16,543 --> 00:04:17,872
- It's all thanks to you. - Right.

101
00:04:17,873 --> 00:04:19,513
I came up with this.

102
00:04:19,773 --> 00:04:20,943
Thank you, Jung Ah.

103
00:04:21,683 --> 00:04:22,683
(Kissing)

104
00:04:22,813 --> 00:04:24,483
I didn't expect this to actually happen.

105
00:04:25,183 --> 00:04:27,453
I have so many things I'm curious about.

106
00:04:27,583 --> 00:04:29,122
These are the things we're curious about.

107
00:04:29,123 --> 00:04:30,429
The place where we'll be going to.

108
00:04:30,453 --> 00:04:32,022
What was it again?

109
00:04:32,023 --> 00:04:34,522
This is a famous place for its Hanoi stew.

110
00:04:34,523 --> 00:04:36,392
- Hanoi? - It must be Vietnam.

111
00:04:36,393 --> 00:04:37,792
(Vietnam?)

112
00:04:37,793 --> 00:04:38,892
Vietnam.

113
00:04:38,893 --> 00:04:40,593
(Peeking)

114
00:04:41,093 --> 00:04:42,962
(The posters of Vietnam come into sight.)

115
00:04:42,963 --> 00:04:44,533
(Vietnamese: Good restaurant, pho)

116
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:47,432
I heard that this place served Thai food.

117
00:04:47,433 --> 00:04:48,472
- Really? - Really?

118
00:04:48,473 --> 00:04:49,703
It might be Thailand, then.

119
00:04:50,003 --> 00:04:53,013
(The Thai dishes on the menu come into mind as well.)

120
00:04:53,543 --> 00:04:56,083
Countries of Southeast Asia are nice...

121
00:04:56,613 --> 00:04:58,283
for a vacation.

122
00:04:58,813 --> 00:05:00,052
Not for work.

123
00:05:00,053 --> 00:05:01,823
(Emphasizing)

124
00:05:02,123 --> 00:05:04,652
(As they are busy predicting the destination, )

125
00:05:04,653 --> 00:05:08,222
(one empty seat comes into sight.)

126
00:05:08,223 --> 00:05:09,863
I think it's a country in Southeast Asia.

127
00:05:10,323 --> 00:05:12,523
Anyway, hurry up and tell us who we will be going with.

128
00:05:12,963 --> 00:05:15,132
(There's one more person.)

129
00:05:15,133 --> 00:05:20,873
This person has worked hard on the show.

130
00:05:21,443 --> 00:05:23,283
It's someone who has already been on the show?

131
00:05:23,643 --> 00:05:24,743
Guess who?

132
00:05:25,473 --> 00:05:28,542
There were so many guests in Season 1 and Season 2.

133
00:05:28,543 --> 00:05:31,452
If it's one of the male guests, could it be Hae Jin? Hwang Jung Min?

134
00:05:31,453 --> 00:05:32,512
Yoon Kyung Ho.

135
00:05:32,513 --> 00:05:34,613
No. I think it's one of the female guests.

136
00:05:34,923 --> 00:05:36,723
- But... - If it's a female guest...

137
00:05:36,953 --> 00:05:40,323
- Hye Yoon and Min Si were guests. - Right.

138
00:05:41,153 --> 00:05:42,793
- Jae Hwa was also a guest. - Right.

139
00:05:42,893 --> 00:05:44,022
I think it's Hye Yoon.

140
00:05:44,023 --> 00:05:45,439
Hye Yoon seems like the strongest candidate.

141
00:05:45,463 --> 00:05:47,263
- Hye Yoon? - She's a great worker.

142
00:05:47,633 --> 00:05:50,132
- She's so cute. - Right.

143
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:51,232
She's so cute.

144
00:05:51,233 --> 00:05:54,102
I've seen her from afar...

145
00:05:54,103 --> 00:05:55,242
- at an event. - Did you?

146
00:05:55,243 --> 00:05:56,272
From afar.

147
00:05:56,273 --> 00:05:57,572
She's really popular.

148
00:05:57,573 --> 00:05:58,972
- She's younger than you. - What?

149
00:05:58,973 --> 00:06:00,073
She's younger than you.

150
00:06:00,373 --> 00:06:01,882
- Really? - She's younger than him?

151
00:06:01,883 --> 00:06:02,883
She's younger.

152
00:06:02,884 --> 00:06:04,583
I've always thought she was my senior.

153
00:06:04,813 --> 00:06:08,112
Will I finally be able to be called an older brother by someone?

154
00:06:08,113 --> 00:06:09,259
You will be getting a younger sister now?

155
00:06:09,283 --> 00:06:11,553
But if she doesn't come,

156
00:06:12,593 --> 00:06:14,393
I might get greatly disappointed.

157
00:06:15,693 --> 00:06:19,793
(One person carefully walks toward the restaurant.)

158
00:06:19,933 --> 00:06:21,603
I'm feeling so nervous.

159
00:06:25,033 --> 00:06:27,033
(Walking lightly)

160
00:06:27,473 --> 00:06:28,503
Hello.

161
00:06:29,443 --> 00:06:30,443
(Oh, my gosh!)

162
00:06:31,073 --> 00:06:33,142
(Who is it?)

163
00:06:33,143 --> 00:06:34,642
See? It's Hye Yoon!

164
00:06:34,643 --> 00:06:37,883
(The new youngest sibling, Kim Hye Yoon)

165
00:06:38,313 --> 00:06:40,783
(Did you know that you're still saved as Ye Seo on my phone?)

166
00:06:40,813 --> 00:06:41,823
Really?

167
00:06:42,023 --> 00:06:44,482
(Jung Ah's precious daughter in "Sky Castle")

168
00:06:44,483 --> 00:06:47,393
(She ate diligently...)

169
00:06:47,493 --> 00:06:51,493
(and worked diligently.)

170
00:06:51,993 --> 00:06:55,333
(After getting Leader Yum's approval, )

171
00:06:55,963 --> 00:06:58,533
(she got listed as one of the top workers.)

172
00:06:59,003 --> 00:07:00,033
Really?

173
00:07:00,773 --> 00:07:02,173
I was chosen as a top worker? Gosh!

174
00:07:02,673 --> 00:07:04,912
I'm feeling so nervous right now.

175
00:07:04,913 --> 00:07:06,513
I will do my best with everything.

176
00:07:06,873 --> 00:07:10,713
Actually, I can't predict what I'll be doing.

177
00:07:11,043 --> 00:07:14,382
Even so, I will make sure to get everything done.

178
00:07:14,383 --> 00:07:15,523
(Clear eyes)

179
00:07:16,253 --> 00:07:17,883
Gosh, hello!

180
00:07:18,693 --> 00:07:20,592
Have you been doing well, Ms. Hye Yoon?

181
00:07:20,593 --> 00:07:21,593
Ms. Hye Yoon?

182
00:07:21,594 --> 00:07:23,262
I wasn't able to fully feel comfortable with her.

183
00:07:23,263 --> 00:07:25,362
- It's been quite some time. - Feel free to speak casually.

184
00:07:25,363 --> 00:07:27,693
Right. I can't believe this.

185
00:07:27,893 --> 00:07:30,132
We were predicting it to be you...

186
00:07:30,133 --> 00:07:31,932
- and you came right in. - Really?

187
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:34,072
We wished for it to be you,

188
00:07:34,073 --> 00:07:35,503
and you really came in. Gosh!

189
00:07:35,603 --> 00:07:37,079
- Thank you. - It's a pleasure to meet you.

190
00:07:37,103 --> 00:07:38,643
I'm looking forward to this.

191
00:07:39,243 --> 00:07:41,012
I heard you were born in 1996.

192
00:07:41,013 --> 00:07:42,783
Right.

193
00:07:43,783 --> 00:07:45,182
He's sorting out the ranks right away.

194
00:07:45,183 --> 00:07:47,852
(Look at him.)

195
00:07:47,853 --> 00:07:48,922
Sorting out the ranks right away.

196
00:07:48,923 --> 00:07:49,982
- That's not it. - Right. I'm the youngest.

197
00:07:49,983 --> 00:07:52,293
- I was born in 1995. - Right.

198
00:07:52,693 --> 00:07:53,792
- He's your older brother. - I'm your older brother.

199
00:07:53,793 --> 00:07:55,593
- Right. - Gosh.

200
00:07:55,893 --> 00:07:57,222
You have a younger sister now.

201
00:07:57,223 --> 00:07:59,863
- I didn't expect this to happen. - He's loving it.

202
00:08:01,063 --> 00:08:03,102
Gosh, look at Kim Jin Young being so happy...

203
00:08:03,103 --> 00:08:04,303
about having a younger sister.

204
00:08:04,363 --> 00:08:06,872
Gosh, he was the youngest for all this time.

205
00:08:06,873 --> 00:08:07,873
(Look at you!)

206
00:08:07,874 --> 00:08:09,314
Right, Yoon. It's great to meet you.

207
00:08:10,403 --> 00:08:12,142
- Gosh. - "Yoon?"

208
00:08:12,143 --> 00:08:14,212
- Old people speak like that. - Yoon.

209
00:08:14,213 --> 00:08:15,282
Hye Yoon.

210
00:08:15,283 --> 00:08:17,543
(We wish for the two to get close soon.)

211
00:08:18,013 --> 00:08:19,112
(The food is here.)

212
00:08:19,113 --> 00:08:20,113
Hello.

213
00:08:20,114 --> 00:08:21,283
What country food is this?

214
00:08:21,483 --> 00:08:23,453
This one is a Thai dish.

215
00:08:23,623 --> 00:08:25,252
The Hanoi stew that will be served last...

216
00:08:25,253 --> 00:08:26,293
is a Vietnamese dish.

217
00:08:27,593 --> 00:08:30,423
(Today's meal is of different countries.)

218
00:08:30,693 --> 00:08:32,093
(Thai dish, pad thai)

219
00:08:32,193 --> 00:08:33,663
(Thai dish, som tam)

220
00:08:33,733 --> 00:08:35,262
(Vietnamese dish, Hanoi stew)

221
00:08:35,263 --> 00:08:36,302
(Stir-fried morning glory...)

222
00:08:36,303 --> 00:08:38,139
(enjoyed in Thailand, Vietnam, and the Philippines)

223
00:08:38,163 --> 00:08:41,473
- It's a country in Southeast Asia. - Right. We have to guess.

224
00:08:42,473 --> 00:08:44,172
- I'm so hungry. Let's dig in. - Right.

225
00:08:44,173 --> 00:08:46,213
- Thank you for the food. - Thank you for the food.

226
00:08:46,543 --> 00:08:47,673
What should I start with?

227
00:08:48,513 --> 00:08:50,182
(Food should come first before predicting the destination.)

228
00:08:50,183 --> 00:08:52,113
(Satisfied)

229
00:08:52,653 --> 00:08:56,583
(Taking a bite)

230
00:08:56,883 --> 00:08:58,522
(Nodding)

231
00:08:58,523 --> 00:08:59,793
- It's good. - Right.

232
00:08:59,993 --> 00:09:01,292
This is so good.

233
00:09:01,293 --> 00:09:02,613
(They are all enjoying the meal.)

234
00:09:02,723 --> 00:09:05,033
Have you been on a lot of variety shows, Hye Yoon?

235
00:09:05,063 --> 00:09:06,563
- Not a lot. - No, right?

236
00:09:06,663 --> 00:09:08,163
Not as much as you, Dex.

237
00:09:09,463 --> 00:09:11,232
"Dex?"

238
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:14,033
(Did you just call me by my name?)

239
00:09:15,943 --> 00:09:17,373
As he's my older brother,

240
00:09:17,843 --> 00:09:19,113
I called him by his name.

241
00:09:19,373 --> 00:09:21,542
What did you say after that? I missed it.

242
00:09:21,543 --> 00:09:23,842
- He just heard his name. - I was called by my name.

243
00:09:23,843 --> 00:09:25,603
- I feel flustered. - That was all he heard.

244
00:09:25,683 --> 00:09:27,629
Did you like it that much when she called you by your name?

245
00:09:27,653 --> 00:09:29,023
He loved it so much.

246
00:09:29,483 --> 00:09:31,353
Don't be acting like a baby.

247
00:09:32,023 --> 00:09:33,752
(Bringing down his head)

248
00:09:33,753 --> 00:09:36,462
I must have a weak spot for being called that way.

249
00:09:36,463 --> 00:09:38,762
- Did it make you feel excited? - I only had men around me.

250
00:09:38,763 --> 00:09:40,269
I only had guys who called out my name.

251
00:09:40,293 --> 00:09:42,102
I never had any younger women to call my name.

252
00:09:42,103 --> 00:09:43,432
(The ex-youngest feels awkward to be an older brother.)

253
00:09:43,433 --> 00:09:46,802
(Hye Yoon is the new youngest as his younger sister.)

254
00:09:46,803 --> 00:09:47,803
Hye Yoon.

255
00:09:48,503 --> 00:09:50,502
I wonder what Hye Yoon is like.

256
00:09:50,503 --> 00:09:51,812
Is she an easy-going person?

257
00:09:51,813 --> 00:09:53,742
She's very easy-going. She's so cute as well.

258
00:09:53,743 --> 00:09:55,312
- She's diligent. - She's diligent?

259
00:09:55,313 --> 00:09:56,993
- Really? - Even if she wasn't an actress,

260
00:09:57,383 --> 00:09:59,664
she would've made her family prosper in any way possible.

261
00:10:00,213 --> 00:10:01,213
Really?

262
00:10:01,823 --> 00:10:03,353
- She isn't sensitive. - Right.

263
00:10:03,623 --> 00:10:05,393
- She eats everything well. - I love her.

264
00:10:06,293 --> 00:10:07,493
Do you know where we're going?

265
