(When the toast bread pops up)

529
00:19:43,503 --> 00:19:46,473
- Snatch it quickly with your mouth. - Grab it?

530
00:19:47,033 --> 00:19:48,973
Wouldn't that make her look ugly?

531
00:19:49,243 --> 00:19:50,442
- That's... - Don't I just have to hold...

532
00:19:50,443 --> 00:19:51,643
my mouth here?

533
00:19:51,743 --> 00:19:52,972
- No? - One of you have to pop it.

534
00:19:52,973 --> 00:19:54,672
One of you have to stand next to her and pop it.

535
00:19:54,673 --> 00:19:56,282
She's in a romantic drama.

536
00:19:56,283 --> 00:19:58,682
- But what about her drama? - At our first meeting...

537
00:19:58,683 --> 00:20:00,052
- You don't have to play. - Will it be okay?

538
00:20:00,053 --> 00:20:01,752
It'll be fine. Can you do it well?

539
00:20:01,753 --> 00:20:03,122
Yes, you can count on me.

540
00:20:03,123 --> 00:20:04,123
The time limit is...

541
00:20:04,124 --> 00:20:05,483
Do you want me to pop it high?

542
00:20:05,583 --> 00:20:07,652
One, two, three.

543
00:20:07,653 --> 00:20:08,852
(Thud)

544
00:20:08,853 --> 00:20:10,622
- Goodness. - I see.

545
00:20:10,623 --> 00:20:12,063
It doesn't pop up.

546
00:20:12,493 --> 00:20:13,633
One, two.

547
00:20:14,593 --> 00:20:15,662
- Wait. - This is hard.

548
00:20:15,663 --> 00:20:17,863
Hye Yoon, keep your head higher.

549
00:20:17,963 --> 00:20:19,532
- High? - Yes, a little higher.

550
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:21,133
- One, two, three. - Here?

551
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:23,972
Shouldn't she snatch it?

552
00:20:23,973 --> 00:20:26,612
- Let me try it once. - You have to snatch it.

553
00:20:26,613 --> 00:20:27,949
- Don't you have to snatch it? - Yes.

554
00:20:27,973 --> 00:20:29,543
One, two, three.

555
00:20:32,143 --> 00:20:34,283
(Biting hard)

556
00:20:35,253 --> 00:20:36,253
(Jiggling)

557
00:20:40,123 --> 00:20:42,623
(A toast bread hunt)

558
00:20:42,823 --> 00:20:44,023
- It worked. - Isn't this it?

559
00:20:44,393 --> 00:20:45,423
Isn't this it?

560
00:20:46,263 --> 00:20:47,263
Is this not it?

561
00:20:47,264 --> 00:20:48,663
You simply grabbed...

562
00:20:48,763 --> 00:20:51,233
the bread from the toaster.

563
00:20:51,703 --> 00:20:52,703
Really?

564
00:20:52,773 --> 00:20:53,872
This is impossible.

565
00:20:53,873 --> 00:20:55,772
- Bring us a better toaster. - This...

566
00:20:55,773 --> 00:20:57,142
- Look, Hye Yoon. - It should pop up.

567
00:20:57,143 --> 00:21:00,043
Look, Hye Yoon. The toast bread pops up like this.

568
00:21:00,443 --> 00:21:02,072
- I see. - It goes high enough.

569
00:21:02,073 --> 00:21:04,512
When it's high in the air...

570
00:21:04,513 --> 00:21:06,483
One, two, three.

571
00:21:06,583 --> 00:21:08,383
(Exclaiming)

572
00:21:11,523 --> 00:21:14,353
(She missed the toast bread right in front of her nose.)

573
00:21:15,653 --> 00:21:16,662
Stay there.

574
00:21:16,663 --> 00:21:17,663
One, two, three.

575
00:21:18,093 --> 00:21:19,462
Gosh, it doesn't work.

576
00:21:19,463 --> 00:21:20,932
Move slightly in this direction.

577
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:22,962
(Feeling uneasy while watching Hye Yoon struggle)

578
00:21:22,963 --> 00:21:24,002
(Thud)

579
00:21:24,003 --> 00:21:25,062
- Gosh. - How is this possible?

580
00:21:25,063 --> 00:21:26,072
Can you do it?

581
00:21:26,073 --> 00:21:27,249
- One, two, three. - Two, three.

582
00:21:27,273 --> 00:21:28,533
(Thud)

583
00:21:28,873 --> 00:21:29,942
Two, three.

584
00:21:29,943 --> 00:21:31,823
(Even the third eldest they counted on failed.)

585
00:21:31,973 --> 00:21:35,073
Can someone who's good at it demonstrate it for us?

586
00:21:35,173 --> 00:21:36,842
- Among them? - Come out.

587
00:21:36,843 --> 00:21:37,843
Please come out...

588
00:21:37,844 --> 00:21:39,712
- This is... - and show us. This isn't easy.

589
00:21:39,713 --> 00:21:40,713
- Please show us. - Show us.

590
00:21:40,714 --> 00:21:42,082
Did anyone succeed?

591
00:21:42,083 --> 00:21:44,023
- Who would succeed? - Who successfully made it?

592
00:21:44,723 --> 00:21:46,022
(Meanwhile, Hye Yoon keeps practicing.)

593
00:21:46,023 --> 00:21:47,152
How is this possible?

594
00:21:47,153 --> 00:21:48,692
Who actually succeeded?

595
00:21:48,693 --> 00:21:49,893
How did you do it?

596
00:21:50,423 --> 00:21:52,593
Please demonstrate and show us how it works.

597
00:21:52,993 --> 00:21:55,392
- All right. Let's try it. - Give it a try.

598
00:21:55,393 --> 00:21:56,753
- Give it a try. - I'll take that.

599
00:21:57,103 --> 00:21:59,203
If they don't make it, give us a coin for free.

600
00:21:59,303 --> 00:22:01,602
- Seriously. This is hard. - If they fail...

601
00:22:01,603 --> 00:22:03,123
If they fail, give us a coin for free.

602
00:22:04,143 --> 00:22:05,242
Give it a try.

603
00:22:05,243 --> 00:22:06,613
They can do it in one go.

604
00:22:07,873 --> 00:22:10,482
How many chances do you want?

605
00:22:10,483 --> 00:22:11,983
- Tell us. - How many?

606
00:22:12,083 --> 00:22:13,252
Do you want ten chances?

607
00:22:13,253 --> 00:22:15,333
(Is this the biggest crisis in the writer's career?)

608
00:22:15,683 --> 00:22:17,183
(Loading the toaster)

609
00:22:18,153 --> 00:22:20,553
(The solemn sound of bread being loaded breaks the silence.)

610
00:22:20,723 --> 00:22:21,723
I'm scared.

611
00:22:26,193 --> 00:22:27,233
I'm scared.

612
00:22:28,093 --> 00:22:29,933
(Success)

613
00:22:38,943 --> 00:22:40,813
(Deeply moved)

614
00:22:41,073 --> 00:22:42,442
So it's possible.

615
00:22:42,443 --> 00:22:44,013
(In awe)

616
00:22:44,443 --> 00:22:45,543
- Gosh. - Goodness.

617
00:22:46,383 --> 00:22:47,553
You're amazing.

618
00:22:48,413 --> 00:22:50,722
Dex, we can do it. Let's practice.

619
00:22:50,723 --> 00:22:53,293
- I saw how she did it. - You did?

620
00:22:53,493 --> 00:22:55,992
- She grabbed this side. - I see.

621
00:22:55,993 --> 00:22:57,823
- The bottom part. - The bottom part?

622
00:22:57,923 --> 00:22:59,539
- She grabbed the bottom. - So it's possible.

623
00:22:59,563 --> 00:23:01,433
One, two, three.

624
00:23:01,893 --> 00:23:03,062
(Thud)

625
00:23:03,063 --> 00:23:04,332
You almost got it.

626
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:06,603
Hye Yoon can do it if you give her one day to practice.

627
00:23:06,903 --> 00:23:08,072
- She's a hard worker. - Right?

628
00:23:08,073 --> 00:23:09,902
- She'd make it no matter what. - Seriously.

629
00:23:09,903 --> 00:23:12,443
How did you do it? Did you practice a lot?

630
00:23:13,713 --> 00:23:16,713
- I get it. - Do you have any advice?

631
00:23:17,013 --> 00:23:19,683
It's better to grab the flat side.

632
00:23:20,053 --> 00:23:21,183
That's all?

633
00:23:22,213 --> 00:23:23,453
I saw that.

634
00:23:24,853 --> 00:23:26,953
Is that all the advice you have?

635
00:23:27,423 --> 00:23:29,053
Is there no cheat sheet?

636
00:23:29,153 --> 00:23:32,493
It's easier to snatch it when the bread is going down.

637
00:23:32,763 --> 00:23:33,992
When it's going down?

638
00:23:33,993 --> 00:23:36,033
Grab it when it's going down instead.

639
00:23:36,433 --> 00:23:37,862
- I see. - When the bread goes down...

640
00:23:37,863 --> 00:23:38,863
Okay.

641
00:23:38,864 --> 00:23:39,879
(Taking the master's advice, she starts anew.)

642
00:23:39,903 --> 00:23:41,803
One, two, three.

643
00:23:42,503 --> 00:23:43,873
(Failed)

644
00:23:44,773 --> 00:23:45,873
My gosh.

645
00:23:46,973 --> 00:23:48,413
Goodness.

646
00:23:49,843 --> 00:23:51,782
- I keep missing it. - You almost got it.

647
00:23:51,783 --> 00:23:53,183
(Trying desperately to avoid labor)

648
00:23:54,313 --> 00:23:55,313
You're so close yet so far.

649
00:23:55,314 --> 00:23:56,323
Almost but not quite.

650
00:23:56,483 --> 00:23:57,983
One, two, three.

651
00:23:58,653 --> 00:24:01,292
(Shouting)

652
00:24:01,293 --> 00:24:02,793
One, two, three.

653
00:24:08,463 --> 00:24:09,733
(Biting)

654
00:24:13,933 --> 00:24:14,933
(Stunned)

655
00:24:14,934 --> 00:24:17,203
Please count this as success.

656
00:24:17,303 --> 00:24:18,842
We'll give credit to her perseverance.

657
00:24:18,843 --> 00:24:19,843
Okay.

658
00:24:19,844 --> 00:24:20,943
We'll give you a coin.

659
00:24:21,273 --> 00:24:22,512
(The result of Dex and Hye Yoon's perseverance)

660
00:24:22,513 --> 00:24:23,683
That was cute.

661
00:24:24,283 --> 00:24:25,283
You made it.

662
00:24:25,883 --> 00:24:27,052
Well done.

663
00:24:27,053 --> 00:24:28,852
- Success. - You're the best.

664
00:24:28,853 --> 00:24:31,152
- Thank you. - Your advice was good.

665
00:24:31,153 --> 00:24:32,453
(Thank you, master.)

666
00:24:32,693 --> 00:24:33,892
- Her advice was good. - Right.

667
00:24:33,893 --> 00:24:35,253
- Perfect. - She was right.

668
00:24:36,063 --> 00:24:37,163
I give you credit for it.

669
00:24:37,493 --> 00:24:38,792
Thank you.

670
00:24:38,793 --> 00:24:40,363
(Hye Yoon won 1 coin.)

671
00:24:40,493 --> 00:24:42,032
You finally made it.

672
00:24:42,033 --> 00:24:44,202
- Seriously. - You made it.

673
00:24:44,203 --> 00:24:45,409
(The top-notch worker who also has persistence)

674
00:24:45,433 --> 00:24:47,502
Here's Excellent Worker Verification Test for Park Jun Myun.

675
00:24:47,503 --> 00:24:48,873
- Please. - We'll start.

676
00:24:49,573 --> 00:24:52,203
Park Jun Myun was commonly known as Sauce Park.

677
00:24:52,503 --> 00:24:54,943
(A master of making sauces)

678
00:24:55,113 --> 00:24:57,413
(A born flavor expert)

679
00:24:57,713 --> 00:24:59,983
(In charge of sense of taste among the siblings)

680
00:25:00,053 --> 00:25:02,483
A customized test for Park Jun Myun is...

681
00:25:02,883 --> 00:25:04,052
on her perfect palate.

682
00:25:04,053 --> 00:25:05,952
(Excellent Worker Verification on her perfect palate)

683
00:25:05,953 --> 00:25:07,423
Jun Myun, it's food tasting.

684
00:25:07,523 --> 00:25:08,992
We'll give you a blindfold.

685
00:25:08,993 --> 00:25:11,262
- Okay. A blindfold. - Oh, my.

686
00:25:11,263 --> 00:25:12,462
Please put on the blindfold.

687
00:25:12,463 --> 00:25:14,092
Do I have to guess what it is with the blindfold on?

688
00:25:14,093 --> 00:25:15,093
Yes.

689
00:25:15,233 --> 00:25:18,502
With the blindfold on, you'll taste a sauce.

690
00:25:18,503 --> 00:25:21,972
You must guess the ingredients in the sauce.

691
00:25:21,973 --> 00:25:23,803
(She must guess 4 ingredients in the sauce.)

692
00:25:24,073 --> 00:25:26,843
Could the three of you make the sauce?

693
00:25:27,113 --> 00:25:28,273
- What do you think? - Sure.

694
00:25:29,413 --> 00:25:30,883
Okay, that sounds good.

695
00:25:31,183 --> 00:25:32,583
Jung Ah, this isn't a penalty.

696
00:25:32,883 --> 00:25:34,252
Don't add something like fish sauce.

697
00:25:34,253 --> 00:25:35,253
Of course not.

698
00:25:35,883 --> 00:25:37,922
Why am I the only one facing such a hardship?

699
00:25:37,923 --> 00:25:39,122
It sounds very difficult.

700
00:25:39,123 --> 00:25:40,652
- Are you okay? - I look like someone abducted.

701
00:25:40,653 --> 00:25:42,122
- Don't do it, Jun Myun. - "Honey."

702
00:25:42,123 --> 00:25:44,563
- Stop it. - "Come and rescue me. Honey."

703
00:25:45,423 --> 00:25:47,469
(Excellent Worker Verification Test, Perfect Palate starts.)

704
00:25:47,493 --> 00:25:48,732
- Jung Ah. - You must add four ingredients.

705
00:25:48,733 --> 00:25:50,373
Let's pick the ones she can guess easily.

706
00:25:51,603 --> 00:25:54,533
(Their hands get busy right away.)

707
00:25:55,173 --> 00:25:57,473
These two would go well together.

708
00:25:57,903 --> 00:25:59,903
- Because they're obvious? - They're very obvious.

709
00:26:00,073 --> 00:26:01,142
Over there.

710
00:26:01,143 --> 00:26:03,343
(They chose sesame oil and wasabi with strong flavors.)

711
00:26:03,483 --> 00:26:04,742
(Now, they need to pick two more.)

712
00:26:04,743 --> 00:26:06,112
(They need a total of 4 ingredients.)

713
00:26:06,113 --> 00:26:07,553
- They can't overlap. - What's this?

714
00:26:07,913 --> 00:26:09,453
(Curry powder?)

715
00:26:10,083 --> 00:26:11,222
(A combination that's hard to imagine)

716
00:26:11,223 --> 00:26:12,253
How about this?

717
00:26:12,353 --> 00:26:14,893
(What kind of sauce are they making?)

718
00:26:15,353 --> 00:26:17,793
We can't use these because their flavors overlap.

719
00:26:19,163 --> 00:26:22,033
(Focusing on ingredients with strong flavors that are easy to guess)

720
00:26:22,093 --> 00:26:24,033
My eyes hurt. Hurry up.

721
00:26:24,163 --> 00:26:26,233
Jung Ah, please hurry.

722
00:26:27,803 --> 00:26:28,803
- What about this? - This...

723
00:26:28,804 --> 00:26:30,143
Won't this be okay?

724
00:26:30,943 --> 00:26:33,643
(They even picked yuzu.)

725
00:26:34,313 --> 00:26:35,573
(Laughing)

726
00:26:36,643 --> 00:26:38,483
These two are strong.

727
00:26:38,983 --> 00:26:40,712
If I get it wrong despite your effort,

728
00:26:40,713 --> 00:26:42,882
- I'd take all the blame. - It's impossible to get it wrong.

729
00:26:42,883 --> 00:26:43,922
Really?

730
00:26:43,923 --> 00:26:45,383
(Laughing)

731
00:26:46,653 --> 00:26:48,922
- Please wait a little longer. - Hurry.

732
00:26:48,923 --> 00:26:50,662
(A clash of overpowering flavors that's impossible to miss)

733
00:26:50,663 --> 00:26:52,022
It's getting frustrating.

734
00:26:52,023 --> 00:26:53,832
(Pouring a lot of sesame oil as Jun Myun rushes them)

735
00:26:53,833 --> 00:26:55,632
Not yet. We're still making it.

736
00:26:55,633 --> 00:26:56,833
We're making a new one.

737
00:26:58,163 --> 00:26:59,803
Is this edible?

738
00:26:59,933 --> 00:27:00,933
"Is this edible?"
- What? - Never mind.

739
00:27:01,934 --> 00:27:03,642
- I can hear everything. - It's nothing.

740
00:27:03,643 --> 00:27:04,843
It's as good as a penalty.

741
00:27:05,673 --> 00:27:06,813
A penalty?

742
00:27:07,613 --> 00:27:08,642
Gosh.

743
00:27:08,643 --> 00:27:11,743
(The color looks okay.)

744
00:27:11,943 --> 00:27:14,853
I will taste it first.

745
00:27:15,453 --> 00:27:18,023
(Food Taster Dex is on the move.)

746
00:27:18,653 --> 00:27:21,223
Is there any hint?

747
00:27:21,953 --> 00:27:23,863
(Moaning)

748
00:27:25,193 --> 00:27:26,533
(Groaning)

749
00:27:30,203 --> 00:27:31,663
(Lingering)

750
00:27:32,503 --> 00:27:35,203
(A flavor that makes you laugh in disbelief)

751
00:27:35,403 --> 00:27:37,043
What is it? I want to know.

752
00:27:37,903 --> 00:27:39,973
I can't wait. Hurry up.

753
00:27:40,673 --> 00:27:42,113
It's so painful.

754
00:27:43,583 --> 00:27:46,383
(The ingredients are opinionated.)

755
00:27:46,683 --> 00:27:47,713
What's going on?

756
00:27:48,013 --> 00:27:49,923
You guys are laughing among yourselves.

757
00:27:50,253 --> 00:27:52,022
I feel left out. Please hurry.

758
00:27:52,023 --> 00:27:53,699
(Meanwhile, she analyzes the taste seriously.)

759
00:27:53,723 --> 00:27:55,492
- I can taste them. - You can?

760
00:27:55,493 --> 00:27:57,323
Okay, here we go.

761
00:27:57,423 --> 00:27:58,562
Here we go.

762
00:27:58,563 --> 00:27:59,793
(The sauce is finally made.)

763
00:28:00,063 --> 00:28:02,233
All right, we left the ingredients.

764
00:28:02,763 --> 00:28:03,803
All right.

765
00:28:04,663 --> 00:28:07,933
(Will Sauce Park be able to guess correctly?)

766
00:28:08,233 --> 00:28:09,603
Do you want a small or a big bite?

767
00:28:09,703 --> 00:28:10,903
Jung Ah, give me a big bite.

768
00:28:11,143 --> 00:28:12,242
- A big bite? - Those are the ingredients?

769
00:28:12,243 --> 00:28:14,363
- Will you be okay? - Yes, these are the ingredients.

770
00:28:15,243 --> 00:28:17,613
(She gets a big bite as she wishes.)

771
00:28:17,743 --> 00:28:19,243
Gosh, that was a big spoonful.

772
00:28:20,713 --> 00:28:23,023
(Is she laughing?)

773
00:28:23,383 --> 00:28:25,523
- Jung Ah, the sauce tastes so good. - Doesn't it?

774
00:28:26,723 --> 00:28:28,052
I made it carelessly, but it tastes good.

775
00:28:28,053 --> 00:28:29,353
(Humming)

776
00:28:29,763 --> 00:28:31,883
- There are 4 ingredients. - There are 4 ingredients.

777
00:28:33,763 --> 00:28:35,263
What is it that I'm chewing?

778
00:28:35,633 --> 00:28:37,433
- What? - There is something crunchy.

779
00:28:39,403 --> 00:28:40,673
What is it that I'm chewing?

780
00:28:41,773 --> 00:28:43,333
Jung Ah, can you give me one more bite?

781
00:28:43,503 --> 00:28:45,142
Why not? Open up.

782
00:28:45,143 --> 00:28:47,673
(No matter how bad it is, she isn't a picky eater.)

783
00:28:50,613 --> 00:28:53,112
- All right, here I go. - Instead of guessing,

784
00:28:53,113 --> 00:28:54,283
just talk to us.

785
00:28:54,613 --> 00:28:56,683
There's wasabi.

786
00:28:57,253 --> 00:28:58,253
Sesame oil.
(Impressed)

787
00:28:59,254 --> 00:29:00,293
Gochujang.

788
00:29:00,693 --> 00:29:02,963
Is it ground sesame that's crunchy?

789
00:29:03,663 --> 00:29:04,992
That's what I have so far.

790
00:29:04,993 --> 00:29:06,593
(We're doomed.)

791
00:29:07,093 --> 00:29:08,563
- Am I wrong? - Yes.

792
00:29:09,033 --> 00:29:10,602
- Am I wrong, Jung Ah? - Yes.

793
00:29:10,603 --> 00:29:11,603
(Laughing)

794
00:29:11,963 --> 00:29:14,533
(Sauce Park's pride hits rock bottom.)

795
00:29:14,773 --> 00:29:17,073
Did you call me Sauce Park?

796
00:29:17,443 --> 00:29:19,473
I'm not Sauce Park after all.

797
00:29:20,013 --> 00:29:21,572
- Listen. Gochujang? - Come on, Jun Myun.

798
00:29:21,573 --> 00:29:23,043
Wait, there's gochujang.

799
00:29:25,283 --> 00:29:27,153
- Am I wrong about gochujang? - Yes.

800
00:29:27,613 --> 00:29:28,613
I see.

801
00:29:29,253 --> 00:29:30,422
What is it that's spicy?

802
00:29:30,423 --> 00:29:32,182
Wasabi. Soy sauce?

803
00:29:32,183 --> 00:29:34,093
No. Could it be chili powder in soy sauce?

804
00:29:34,393 --> 00:29:35,593
Is soy sauce spicy?

805
00:29:35,723 --> 00:29:38,963
(Laughing)

806
00:29:39,123 --> 00:29:40,432
What do you think that's crunchy?

807
00:29:40,433 --> 00:29:41,893
Yes, there's something crunchy.

808
00:29:42,463 --> 00:29:43,983
Jung Ah, can I taste it one more time?

809
00:29:45,463 --> 00:29:46,503
Jun Myun.

810
00:29:47,473 --> 00:29:48,473
(Opening)

811
00:29:49,603 --> 00:29:50,702
(Opening up for the 3rd time already)

812
00:29:50,703 --> 00:29:52,403
Try to taste what's crunchy.

813
00:29:52,803 --> 00:29:53,842
(Humming)

814
00:29:53,843 --> 00:29:55,313
How is it? What do you think it is?

815
00:29:55,773 --> 00:29:58,883
(Please...)

816
00:29:59,483 --> 00:30:00,653
Yuzu.

817
00:30:01,283 --> 00:30:02,482
In that case...

818
00:30:02,483 --> 00:30:04,223
Organize your thoughts for a moment.

819
00:30:05,183 --> 00:30:07,093
Yuzu, wasabi.

820
00:30:07,653 --> 00:30:09,253
Sesame oil, gochujang.

821
00:30:09,553 --> 00:30:10,563
No.

822
00:30:11,493 --> 00:30:12,663
- Jun Myun. - Gochujang.

823
00:30:13,363 --> 00:30:14,892
(Stop bringing up chili.)

824
00:30:14,893 --> 00:30:15,933
Jun Myun.

825
00:30:16,503 --> 00:30:17,633
It's difficult.

826
00:30:17,963 --> 00:30:19,643
For the last one, we'll do a tactile game.

827
00:30:19,773 --> 00:30:21,773
Give her a tactile hint for the last ingredient.

828
00:30:22,073 --> 00:30:24,193
Seriously, Jun Myun. Give me the tip of your fingers.

829
00:30:24,573 --> 00:30:25,603
Jun Myun.

830
00:30:26,513 --> 00:30:28,173
I'm telling you. It's not gochujang.

831
00:30:29,573 --> 00:30:30,842
Jun Myun, it's not gochujang.

832
00:30:30,843 --> 00:30:32,642
- It's a tactile game. - Okay.

833
00:30:32,643 --> 00:30:35,113
(Putting curry powder gently on her hand)

834
00:30:35,483 --> 00:30:36,523
Is it powder?

835
00:30:37,653 --> 00:30:38,752
Chili powder?

836
00:30:38,753 --> 00:30:39,753
(Then is it chili powder?)

837
00:30:39,754 --> 00:30:40,793
No, it's not.

838
00:30:42,693 --> 00:30:43,923
Think about the taste.

839
00:30:44,693 --> 00:30:46,693
I can smell it every time you talk.

840
00:30:47,593 --> 00:30:48,963
Tell us what that is.

841
00:30:49,333 --> 00:30:50,402
(The smell?)

842
00:30:50,403 --> 00:30:52,662
Check your breath. Smell it.

843
00:30:52,663 --> 00:30:54,773
Garlic? No, is it garlic powder?

844
00:30:55,833 --> 00:30:59,403
(She can't smell it even when she puts her hand out.)

845
00:30:59,503 --> 00:31:00,813
Did you catch a cold?

846
00:31:01,243 --> 00:31:02,413
Do you have a sinus cold?

847
00:31:02,743 --> 00:31:03,843
Onion powder?

848
00:31:04,813 --> 00:31:07,212
It must be some kind of onion powder.

849
00:31:07,213 --> 00:31:08,413
(Guessing all types of powder)

850
00:31:08,653 --> 00:31:11,223
- How did you make sauces until now? - Onion...

851
00:31:12,583 --> 00:31:14,022
I want to see it fast.

852
00:31:14,023 --> 00:31:15,469
(She's the only one who can't smell it.)

853
00:31:15,493 --> 00:31:16,563
Jung Ah.

854
00:31:16,763 --> 00:31:18,923
I want to find out right now.

855
00:31:19,733 --> 00:31:21,292
- Taste it one more time. - No.

856
00:31:21,293 --> 00:31:23,632
- Hurry and eat it. - Give me a hint instead.

857
00:31:23,633 --> 00:31:24,663
Goodness.

858
00:31:26,533 --> 00:31:29,173
(This time, she gives it to her nose.)

859
00:31:31,243 --> 00:31:32,972
Jung Ah, I went to a beauty salon today.

860
00:31:32,973 --> 00:31:34,173
You keep...

861
00:31:34,673 --> 00:31:36,713
(Rudolph's curry nose)

862
00:31:37,143 --> 00:31:39,283
Wipe your nose.

863
00:31:40,013 --> 00:31:42,412
Try to smell the last ingredient.

864
00:31:42,413 --> 00:31:43,823
(Please say curry.)

865
00:31:44,553 --> 00:31:45,653
Ground sesame?

866
00:31:46,423 --> 00:31:47,423
(Giving up)

867
00:31:48,553 --> 00:31:50,063
As a hint...

868
00:31:50,463 --> 00:31:52,893
Give her one word as a hint.

869
00:31:53,193 --> 00:31:54,962
I'll do it.

870
00:31:54,963 --> 00:31:55,963
- Jun Myun. - Yes?

871
00:31:55,964 --> 00:31:57,433
- Please concentrate. - Okay.

872
00:31:58,303 --> 00:31:59,333
India.

873
00:32:01,003 --> 00:32:02,073
Curry.

874
00:32:02,533 --> 00:32:04,642
(A feeling of a blockage being cleared)

875
00:32:04,643 --> 00:32:06,072
- Correct. - Could you say answer...

876
00:32:06,073 --> 00:32:07,313
and say the four ingredients?

877
00:32:07,513 --> 00:32:09,513
Answer. Wasabi,

878
00:32:10,343 --> 00:32:13,613
yuzu, sesame oil, curry.

879
00:32:14,153 --> 00:32:15,212
Correct.

880
00:32:15,213 --> 00:32:17,323
(Answer: Wasabi, yuzu, sesame oil, curry powder)

881
00:32:17,823 --> 00:32:19,323
That was really...

882
00:32:19,823 --> 00:32:20,823
Goodness.

883
00:32:20,824 --> 00:32:24,393
I couldn't taste the curry powder at all, Jung Ah.

884
00:32:24,563 --> 00:32:26,492
- I couldn't taste it at all. - I can smell it.

885
00:32:26,493 --> 00:32:27,832
I thought that it was perilla seed powder.

886
00:32:27,833 --> 00:32:29,232
Perilla seed powder also has a smell.

887
00:32:29,233 --> 00:32:30,763
Anyway, thank you.

888
00:32:31,333 --> 00:32:33,403
To be honest, the production crew let us...

889
00:32:34,033 --> 00:32:36,302
win this one.

890
00:32:36,303 --> 00:32:38,643
Thank you. You gave us one for free.

891
00:32:38,873 --> 00:32:41,212
Thank you. We got one more.

892
00:32:41,213 --> 00:32:43,983
- Jun Myun, you worked very hard. - Thank you.

893
00:32:44,483 --> 00:32:46,242
(It was followed by Leader Yum's skill verification test.)

894
00:32:46,243 --> 00:32:48,012
(Spilling)

895
00:32:48,013 --> 00:32:49,823
- Isn't it sour? - It must be very sour.

896
00:32:50,053 --> 00:32:51,122
It's very sour.

897
00:32:51,123 --> 00:32:52,482
(It was followed by Leader Yum's skill verification test.)

898
00:32:52,483 --> 00:32:53,752
(Failed)

899
00:32:53,753 --> 00:32:55,023
It didn't work.

900
00:32:56,623 --> 00:32:58,363
She almost made it.

901
00:32:59,293 --> 00:33:00,633
- That's a bummer. - Forget it.

902
00:33:01,133 --> 00:33:02,362
- Then... - It couldn't be helped.

903
00:33:02,363 --> 00:33:03,933
- do we have three coins? - Yes.

904
00:33:04,433 --> 00:33:05,933
That's not so bad.

905
00:33:06,033 --> 00:33:08,773
- We only have to work two days. - Right.

906
00:33:08,873 --> 00:33:11,003
- That's okay. - You can remove cooking.

907
00:33:11,103 --> 00:33:12,902
- No, we'll just cook. - Why would we remove cooking?

908
00:33:12,903 --> 00:33:15,213
- We'll cook. - Let's remove labor.

909
00:33:15,943 --> 00:33:17,443
Let's take out three days of labor.

910
00:33:18,013 --> 00:33:19,382
- Shall I draw them? - Yes.

911
00:33:19,383 --> 00:33:20,752
(It's time to draw activities from the drawing machine.)

912
00:33:20,753 --> 00:33:21,953
I'll draw them.

913
00:33:23,283 --> 00:33:25,783
(Inserting 3 coins)

914
00:33:26,623 --> 00:33:28,423
(He gets 3 capsules.)

915
00:33:30,793 --> 00:33:32,353
(He tries to get another one by force.)

916
00:33:32,823 --> 00:33:34,733
- What are you doing? - It doesn't work?

917
00:33:35,193 --> 00:33:37,262
- I tried to get one more. - All right.

918
00:33:37,263 --> 00:33:39,632
- Here you go, Hye Yoon. - Take a look 1 by 1.

919
00:33:39,633 --> 00:33:40,873
- One. - Goodness.

920
00:33:41,233 --> 00:33:42,603
- Shall I go first? - Yes.

921
00:33:43,003 --> 00:33:44,142
(Full Body Massage Coupon, Local Health Food Experience)

922
00:33:44,143 --> 00:33:45,572
(Which activities did the siblings draw?)

923
00:33:45,573 --> 00:33:47,042
(Fine Dining Voucher, Dud, Cheap Dining Voucher)

924
00:33:47,043 --> 00:33:48,919
(Foot Massage Coupon, Mid-Range Dining Voucher)

925
00:33:48,943 --> 00:33:50,013
Dex.

926
00:33:50,913 --> 00:33:52,289
- Jun Myun, you look at it. - Okay.

927
00:33:52,313 --> 00:33:53,483
What will it be?

928
00:33:54,083 --> 00:33:55,683
(The long-awaited first activity)

929
00:33:55,913 --> 00:33:57,453
"Dances with Turtles."

930
00:33:59,253 --> 00:34:00,523
"Dances with Turtles."

931
00:34:03,523 --> 00:34:06,693
(Dances with Turtles)

932
00:34:06,893 --> 00:34:08,462
There are so many good ones.

933
00:34:08,463 --> 00:34:10,343
Why would we dance with turtles? That's random.

934
00:34:11,233 --> 00:34:12,563
- What do you have? - Goodness.

935
00:34:13,173 --> 00:34:14,203
Gosh.

936
00:34:15,473 --> 00:34:17,503
- What is it? - It's so annoying.

937
00:34:17,743 --> 00:34:19,473
- What is it? - Show it to them.

938
00:34:20,473 --> 00:34:22,012
(The second activity in Jung Ah's hands)

939
00:34:22,013 --> 00:34:23,842
- Fun... - Exploration of Local Crops.

940
00:34:23,843 --> 00:34:26,143
Additional Exploration of Local Crops.

941
00:34:29,923 --> 00:34:33,293
(Fun Additional Exploration of Local Crops)

942
00:34:33,693 --> 00:34:35,522
Did you do this on purpose?

943
00:34:35,523 --> 00:34:36,692
- No way. - It's strange.

944
00:34:36,693 --> 00:34:38,763
What if the massage coupons are on top?

945
00:34:39,493 --> 00:34:40,662
Shall I open it?

946
00:34:40,663 --> 00:34:42,103
(Opening the last activity in doubt)

947
00:34:42,533 --> 00:34:44,433
- "Dive into the Jungle." - I knew it.

948
00:34:46,773 --> 00:34:50,703
(Dive into the Jungle)

949
00:34:50,903 --> 00:34:51,942
What do we do?

950
00:34:51,943 --> 00:34:53,712
- These are penalties. - How...

951
00:34:53,713 --> 00:34:55,442
It was useless to win the games.

952
00:34:55,443 --> 00:34:57,019
- I know. - There are restaurant vouchers too.

953
00:34:57,043 --> 00:34:58,713
Are these really good?

954
00:34:59,413 --> 00:35:02,183
The capsules come out in order.

955
00:35:02,653 --> 00:35:04,783
- Then draw some more. - Go ahead and draw two more.

956
00:35:05,853 --> 00:35:07,223
(She does it right away.)

957
00:35:07,553 --> 00:35:09,433
We have a hard time trusting people. I'm sorry.

958
00:35:09,853 --> 00:35:12,522
- We tend to be suspicious. - We've been tricked so many times.

959
00:35:12,523 --> 00:35:14,563
- We need to live a little. - It's hard to believe.

960
00:35:15,263 --> 00:35:17,132
You got it?

961
00:35:17,133 --> 00:35:20,303
(What activity will it be?)

962
00:35:21,273 --> 00:35:23,573
Full Rental of a Private Island.

963
00:35:23,903 --> 00:35:25,043
(Surprised)

964
00:35:25,573 --> 00:35:27,242
- That's a good one. - It did come out.

965
00:35:27,243 --> 00:35:29,642
Full rental...

966
00:35:29,643 --> 00:35:31,113
of a private island?

967
00:35:31,613 --> 00:35:34,752
We'll bring this drawing machine when we go abroad.

968
00:35:34,753 --> 00:35:36,152
(I see.)

969
00:35:36,153 --> 00:35:37,482
That changes everything.

970
00:35:37,483 --> 00:35:39,403
(We still have a chance to change the schedule.)

971
00:35:39,583 --> 00:35:42,653
(The game to avoid labor continues even on vacation.)

972
00:35:42,923 --> 00:35:44,763
(I will complete the mission.)

973
00:35:45,023 --> 00:35:47,039
(Fresh off the Sea has changed completely as they go aboard.)

974
00:35:47,063 --> 00:35:48,333
(Please taste it, My Lady.)

975
00:35:48,493 --> 00:35:50,203
(All right.)

976
00:35:52,063 --> 00:35:53,063
Darn it.

977
00:35:53,233 --> 00:35:54,633
(Laughing)

978
00:35:54,973 --> 00:35:58,603
(They are livelier and louder.)

979
00:35:58,943 --> 00:35:59,943
(Don't say that...)

980
00:35:59,944 --> 00:36:01,412
(with your lips so red.)

981
00:36:01,413 --> 00:36:02,413
(It's scary.)

982
00:36:02,813 --> 00:36:04,589
(The new and spicier Fresh off the Sea is here!)

983
00:36:04,613 --> 00:36:07,513
Now, we can push these away. Am I right?

984
00:36:07,683 --> 00:36:09,053
Now, we'll begin.

985
00:36:09,953 --> 00:36:12,353
- We picked these three. - Yes.

986
00:36:12,523 --> 00:36:14,523
- We... - Can we push three tasks away?

987
00:36:14,653 --> 00:36:17,263
We can go for something like this.

988
00:36:17,663 --> 00:36:19,192
How are we going to allocate these?

989
00:36:19,193 --> 00:36:20,662
When do you want to work?

990
00:36:20,663 --> 00:36:22,162
I don't want any labor on the first day.

991
00:36:22,163 --> 00:36:23,332
- On the first day? - Right.

992
00:36:23,333 --> 00:36:25,462
But if we work on our first day,

993
00:36:25,463 --> 00:36:26,902
we only have one day left for labor.

994
00:36:26,903 --> 00:36:28,032
- For labor? - Yes.

995
00:36:28,033 --> 00:36:29,033
Okay, then.

996
00:36:29,034 --> 00:36:31,142
- We'll work on the first day. - Yes.

997
00:36:31,143 --> 00:36:33,512
We'll work and cook. Does it sound okay?

998
00:36:33,513 --> 00:36:34,513
- Yes. - Yes.

999
00:36:34,514 --> 00:36:36,142
We'll cheer up and do them both while we still have energy.

1000
00:36:36,143 --> 00:36:38,143
Yes. We don't know when we'll collapse.

1001
00:36:39,243 --> 00:36:41,853
- You're right, Jung Ah. - On our second day...

1002
00:36:42,083 --> 00:36:43,622
On the second day,

1003
00:36:43,623 --> 00:36:46,182
let's take it easy and see how it feels.

1004
00:36:46,183 --> 00:36:48,522
On the second day, the jungle...

1005
00:36:48,523 --> 00:36:49,953
Should we dance with turtles?

1006
00:36:49,993 --> 00:36:52,092
- Dances with Turtles are... - Do we have to...

1007
00:36:52,093 --> 00:36:53,992
- leave at dawn to do that? - I heard it was fun.

1008
00:36:53,993 --> 00:36:56,132
Exactly. Turtles have their own biorhythms.

1009
00:36:56,133 --> 00:36:57,133
You're right.

1010
00:36:58,103 --> 00:37:00,302
We have to cast the turtles.

1011
00:37:00,303 --> 00:37:01,672
- We won't leave at dawn. - Right.

1012
00:37:01,673 --> 00:37:03,603
- Yes. - We should take our time.

1013
00:37:03,673 --> 00:37:04,742
Like this.

1014
00:37:04,743 --> 00:37:06,673
On our second day, Dances with Turtles.

1015
00:37:07,143 --> 00:37:09,172
I think we should go to the jungle...

1016
00:37:09,173 --> 00:37:10,742
- when we have any energy left. - You're right.

1017
00:37:10,743 --> 00:37:11,882
That's the way to go.

1018
00:37:11,883 --> 00:37:13,412
(On the 4th day, Dive into the Jungle)

1019
00:37:13,413 --> 00:37:14,752
On the last day...

1020
00:37:14,753 --> 00:37:16,112
We can explore lazily.

1021
00:37:16,113 --> 00:37:17,152
Yes, we can.

1022
00:37:17,153 --> 00:37:18,322
(Jung Ah's mindset)

1023
00:37:18,323 --> 00:37:21,823
- Jung Ah. Okay. - We'll schedule it like this.

1024
00:37:23,393 --> 00:37:25,662
(They'll fill up the schedule with various tasks overseas too.)

1025
00:37:25,663 --> 00:37:27,893
- With that... - With this, it's still a holiday.

1026
00:37:28,363 --> 00:37:30,602
Aren't you really going to tell us where we're going...

1027
00:37:30,603 --> 00:37:32,063
when we're heading home now?

1028
00:37:32,963 --> 00:37:35,333
- We missed it. - I'll look for it.

1029
00:37:36,973 --> 00:37:38,203
It's the Maldives, isn't it?

1030
00:37:39,043 --> 00:37:40,912
(Laughing)

1031
00:37:40,913 --> 00:37:42,943
Gosh. You didn't fall for it.

1032
00:37:43,443 --> 00:37:44,942
- Good job. - Well done.

1033
00:37:44,943 --> 00:37:46,242
- Nice work. - Good job.

1034
00:37:46,243 --> 00:37:47,882
- Do we meet at the airport, then? - Yes.

1035
00:37:47,883 --> 00:37:49,563
(The chaotic pre-meeting comes to an end.)

1036
00:37:50,553 --> 00:37:53,692
(Incheon International Airport after several weeks)

1037
00:37:53,693 --> 00:37:55,792
Hello.

1038
00:37:55,793 --> 00:37:58,923
(The youngest Hye Yoon is the first to arrive.)

1039
00:38:00,023 --> 00:38:01,032
(Pushing)

1040
00:38:01,033 --> 00:38:02,963
I think I packed too much. Gosh.

1041
00:38:03,403 --> 00:38:05,362
It's so heavy. It's hard to manage.

1042
00:38:05,363 --> 00:38:06,679
(She has come with a suitcase as big as her.)

1043
00:38:06,703 --> 00:38:09,233
I have this "what-if" syndrome.

1044
00:38:10,203 --> 00:38:12,302
I mean, my backpack is so heavy too.

1045
00:38:12,303 --> 00:38:14,273
I have so much in my carry-on bag.

1046
00:38:14,743 --> 00:38:16,373
I'm the youngest one.

1047
00:38:16,643 --> 00:38:19,743
So I'll have to move around...

1048
00:38:19,883 --> 00:38:22,013
hurriedly and diligently.

1049
00:38:22,553 --> 00:38:24,282
I'm so worried to be honest.

1050
00:38:24,283 --> 00:38:25,382
(She's filled with worries like her bag is filled with stuff.)

1051
00:38:25,383 --> 00:38:27,153
I should do well as the youngest.

1052
00:38:28,623 --> 00:38:30,522
Gosh. I'm nervous.

1053
00:38:30,523 --> 00:38:33,003
(While the youngest is excited and nervous at the same time, )

1054
00:38:33,493 --> 00:38:38,263
(the former youngest one, who is looking fine yet, is here.)

1055
00:38:39,203 --> 00:38:40,873
