1300
00:48:09,319 --> 00:48:10,988
- A son. - I see.

1301
00:48:10,989 --> 00:48:12,519
Gosh. He said "son" in Korean.

1302
00:48:13,789 --> 00:48:15,589
Brother, how old are you?

1303
00:48:16,329 --> 00:48:18,428
- I'm 32. No, I'm 31. - Are you 31 years old?

1304
00:48:18,429 --> 00:48:19,758
- Yes. - Is he 31 years old?

1305
00:48:19,759 --> 00:48:21,928
- You're a big brother. - Yes.

1306
00:48:21,929 --> 00:48:23,105
(Now, the former youngest brother has become a big brother.)

1307
00:48:23,129 --> 00:48:25,168
- Are you 30 years old? - I am.

1308
00:48:25,169 --> 00:48:26,199
Are you 30 now?

1309
00:48:26,899 --> 00:48:28,909
I won't tell you my age.

1310
00:48:29,269 --> 00:48:30,715
(The eldest sister's age is a secret.)

1311
00:48:30,739 --> 00:48:33,438
- Mark, you're the youngest. - The youngest.

1312
00:48:33,439 --> 00:48:36,078
- Yes. You're a little brother. - A little brother.

1313
00:48:36,079 --> 00:48:37,639
(Dex's second younger sibling is Mark.)

1314
00:48:37,719 --> 00:48:40,378
(The sky is getting brighter in Bohol.)

1315
00:48:40,379 --> 00:48:41,788
- Gosh. - Good.

1316
00:48:41,789 --> 00:48:43,488
- My eyes. - Gosh. My eyes.

1317
00:48:43,489 --> 00:48:44,765
(As the morning sunlight penetrates into the car, )

1318
00:48:44,789 --> 00:48:48,159
(he puts on their sunglasses.)

1319
00:48:48,459 --> 00:48:50,459
What's famous in Bohol, Mark?

1320
00:48:50,559 --> 00:48:51,859
- In Bohol? - Yes.

1321
00:48:52,099 --> 00:48:53,628
(What are the local specialties in Bohol?)

1322
00:48:53,629 --> 00:48:55,968
- Well... - What is it famous for?

1323
00:48:55,969 --> 00:48:57,298
(Reading the room)

1324
00:48:57,299 --> 00:48:58,568
I can't really speak Korean.

1325
00:48:58,569 --> 00:49:01,108
- Like pineapples. What's famous? - What's famous?

1326
00:49:01,109 --> 00:49:04,209
- Famous... - What's the most famous in Bohol?

1327
00:49:04,509 --> 00:49:06,879
Well...

1328
00:49:06,979 --> 00:49:10,108
- Pineapples? Or durians? - Durians?

1329
00:49:10,109 --> 00:49:11,179
I don't know.

1330
00:49:11,479 --> 00:49:13,849
(Why doesn't he know what's famous when he's a local?)

1331
00:49:14,549 --> 00:49:16,749
(Jung Ah observes him carefully.)

1332
00:49:16,849 --> 00:49:18,419
(Grinning)

1333
00:49:18,559 --> 00:49:22,489
The staff told him not to tell us.

1334
00:49:22,789 --> 00:49:23,828
Really?

1335
00:49:23,829 --> 00:49:26,628
- They told him not to tell us. - "You don't know?"

1336
00:49:26,629 --> 00:49:27,929
- You... - My goodness.

1337
00:49:28,229 --> 00:49:30,469
Gosh. You said, "I don't know."

1338
00:49:31,069 --> 00:49:33,099
- They hushed him up. - Exactly.

1339
00:49:34,309 --> 00:49:35,309
- It didn't make sense. - That's why...

1340
00:49:35,310 --> 00:49:37,655
He'll say he doesn't speak Korean when we ask such questions.

1341
00:49:37,679 --> 00:49:38,709
Do you get it?

1342
00:49:39,379 --> 00:49:41,248
- Come on, Mark. - Mark.

1343
00:49:41,249 --> 00:49:44,079
- Little brother. - My goodness.

1344
00:49:44,379 --> 00:49:46,778
- Where are we going? - It's a secret.

1345
00:49:46,779 --> 00:49:49,218
- "A secret." - I don't know.

1346
00:49:49,219 --> 00:49:51,388
- Tell us. - I don't know.

1347
00:49:51,389 --> 00:49:53,289
- Gosh. Mark. - "I don't know?" You're busted.

1348
00:49:54,559 --> 00:49:55,628
I thought he really didn't know.

1349
00:49:55,629 --> 00:49:57,388
- "Why doesn't he know it?" - I thought so too.

1350
00:49:57,389 --> 00:49:58,998
But that wasn't the case.

1351
00:49:58,999 --> 00:50:00,335
(The siblings were fooled by Mark.)

1352
00:50:00,359 --> 00:50:02,598
Look at Hye Yoon braiding her hair, Jung Ah.

1353
00:50:02,599 --> 00:50:03,868
- Adorable. - She's so cute.

1354
00:50:03,869 --> 00:50:06,599
(The youngest one is getting adored.)

1355
00:50:06,669 --> 00:50:08,038
- My hair will get uncontrollable. - Right.

1356
00:50:08,039 --> 00:50:09,538
- So I braided it. - Okay.

1357
00:50:09,539 --> 00:50:10,868
- Good job. - I'm the treasurer.

1358
00:50:10,869 --> 00:50:12,508
- I'll count the money. - Okay. Let's do that.

1359
00:50:12,509 --> 00:50:13,679
- Count money. - My eyes.

1360
00:50:14,009 --> 00:50:15,778
- Right. It's so bright. - Hold on.

1361
00:50:15,779 --> 00:50:18,018
What's the currency here?

1362
00:50:18,019 --> 00:50:20,978
How much is it? I have no clue.

1363
00:50:20,979 --> 00:50:21,988
Right?

1364
00:50:21,989 --> 00:50:24,019
- So, one peso... - I have no clue.

1365
00:50:24,559 --> 00:50:26,489
- Yes. - is 2.5 cents.

1366
00:50:26,989 --> 00:50:30,628
But I don't have a clue how much it's worth here.

1367
00:50:30,629 --> 00:50:32,228
- The costs here? - Yes.

1368
00:50:32,229 --> 00:50:33,229
(Now, the cost of living is the issue.)

1369
00:50:33,230 --> 00:50:34,368
- Mark. - Yes?

1370
00:50:34,369 --> 00:50:37,229
How much does a bottle of water cost here?

1371
00:50:38,239 --> 00:50:39,868
- It's 15 pesos. - Is it 15?

1372
00:50:39,869 --> 00:50:41,568
- Yes. - It's 37.5 cents.

1373
00:50:41,569 --> 00:50:43,709
- It's about 40 cents, then. - I see. It's 40 cents.

1374
00:50:44,009 --> 00:50:46,608
A bottle of water in Korea costs...

1375
00:50:46,609 --> 00:50:48,008
- about 1.2 dollars, right? - At a convenience store,

1376
00:50:48,009 --> 00:50:50,779
It costs about 1 dollar or 1.5 dollars.

1377
00:50:51,249 --> 00:50:53,849
It's about one-third or one-quarter here.

1378
00:50:54,649 --> 00:50:56,889
(While the big sisters calculate the cost of water, )

1379
00:50:57,819 --> 00:51:00,919
(Hye Yoon counts the money.)

1380
00:51:01,589 --> 00:51:02,589
- Gosh. - It's 5,000.

1381
00:51:02,590 --> 00:51:04,028
- We have to combine it. - It had about 4,000 pesos before.

1382
00:51:04,029 --> 00:51:06,458
- They gave us 10,000 pesos. - Yes.

1383
00:51:06,459 --> 00:51:08,168
- How much is 10,000 pesos? - Yes.

1384
00:51:08,169 --> 00:51:10,668
- If it's 10,000 pesos... - It's 250 dollars.

1385
00:51:10,669 --> 00:51:12,639
It's 250 dollars and 30 cents.

1386
00:51:12,869 --> 00:51:14,068
- Gosh. - Is it 250 dollars and 30 cents?

1387
00:51:14,069 --> 00:51:15,109
That's a lot.

1388
00:51:15,709 --> 00:51:18,509
I'll hold on to 2,000 pesos for today.

1389
00:51:19,239 --> 00:51:21,908
I'm worried when I think this might be all we'll have.

1390
00:51:21,909 --> 00:51:24,379
Right. That's why the treasurer is important.

1391
00:51:25,279 --> 00:51:28,288
It's our first day.

1392
00:51:28,289 --> 00:51:30,018
We'll stay here for about five days.

1393
00:51:30,019 --> 00:51:31,518
- Yes. - That's right.

1394
00:51:31,519 --> 00:51:34,689
We have to set a limit on our daily spending.

1395
00:51:34,929 --> 00:51:37,558
Our members are on top of everything,

1396
00:51:37,559 --> 00:51:38,958
so I feel so comfortable, Jung Ah.

1397
00:51:38,959 --> 00:51:41,799
Exactly. I'm relaxed right now.

1398
00:51:42,929 --> 00:51:45,498
I couldn't have left it to you, Jun Myun.

1399
00:51:45,499 --> 00:51:47,668
You're right. Don't give me any responsibilities.

1400
00:51:47,669 --> 00:51:48,809
Gosh. She is...

1401
00:51:49,009 --> 00:51:51,379
- I... - We don't know what she'll eat.

1402
00:51:52,339 --> 00:51:57,179
I'm someone who eats enthusiastically.

1403
00:51:57,779 --> 00:52:00,118
That's who I am.

1404
00:52:00,119 --> 00:52:01,519
(Everyone on the show is precious.)

1405
00:52:02,719 --> 00:52:05,459
(They've been on the road for 40 minutes already.)

1406
00:52:06,959 --> 00:52:07,959
Are we almost there?

1407
00:52:09,229 --> 00:52:10,259
It's a secret.

1408
00:52:11,259 --> 00:52:12,328
No.

1409
00:52:12,329 --> 00:52:14,358
(His answer, secret, comes back like a boomerang.)

1410
00:52:14,359 --> 00:52:16,499
I just asked Mark...

1411
00:52:16,969 --> 00:52:18,868
if we're almost there, but he said it's a secret.

1412
00:52:18,869 --> 00:52:20,939
He's determined not to tell us anything.

1413
00:52:21,639 --> 00:52:24,068
- He maintains tight security. - He's impenetrable.

1414
00:52:24,069 --> 00:52:25,579
Mark. Okay.

1415
00:52:25,679 --> 00:52:29,108
We just have to wait until we get there.

1416
00:52:29,109 --> 00:52:31,778
With your tightly sealed mouth, you get a pass.

1417
00:52:31,779 --> 00:52:32,779
He passed.

1418
00:52:32,780 --> 00:52:34,048
(Passed)

1419
00:52:34,049 --> 00:52:36,718
- "Secret." - Secret.

1420
00:52:36,719 --> 00:52:39,019
Gosh. You're good, Mark.

1421
00:52:39,559 --> 00:52:41,489
(Before they know it, the car enters a forest.)

1422
00:52:41,689 --> 00:52:44,059
Where on earth are we going that is this far?

1423
00:52:44,229 --> 00:52:45,229
Where on earth is it?

1424
00:52:45,230 --> 00:52:46,558
It won't be the sea.

1425
00:52:46,559 --> 00:52:48,528
I don't see the sea at all.

1426
00:52:48,529 --> 00:52:50,498
Don't you feel like we're going upward?

1427
00:52:50,499 --> 00:52:52,619
Right. It feels like we're heading toward a mountain.

1428
00:52:53,669 --> 00:52:54,938
Right, Jung Ah? We're going upward.

1429
00:52:54,939 --> 00:52:56,409
Do you smell durians?

1430
00:52:57,109 --> 00:53:00,679
Don't tell me we're picking durians today. No way.

1431
00:53:01,679 --> 00:53:03,379
(Durians suddenly come to their minds.)

1432
00:53:04,209 --> 00:53:07,279
(Wil they really be harvesting the Filipino crops?)

1433
00:53:07,379 --> 00:53:09,448
Why did they give us the waterproof bags, then?

1434
00:53:09,449 --> 00:53:10,588
We'll right a boat.

1435
00:53:10,589 --> 00:53:13,458
Waterproof bags? Right. The one covering the mic.

1436
00:53:13,459 --> 00:53:16,328
Yes. They covered it with a waterproof bag.

1437
00:53:16,329 --> 00:53:18,558
What kind of work are we going to do?

1438
00:53:18,559 --> 00:53:19,798
(They have no idea...)

1439
00:53:19,799 --> 00:53:21,439
(what their first work overseas will be.)

1440
00:53:22,869 --> 00:53:25,739
(It has been 1 hour since they hit the road.)

1441
00:53:26,769 --> 00:53:28,739
It's 7:06am right now.

1442
00:53:29,709 --> 00:53:31,508
(Mark's car is entering somewhere.)

1443
00:53:31,509 --> 00:53:34,409
Abatan?

1444
00:53:34,509 --> 00:53:35,509
What?

1445
00:53:35,609 --> 00:53:37,849
What? It's a river.

1446
00:53:37,949 --> 00:53:41,019
Gosh. What is that? Is that a river or a sea?

1447
00:53:41,179 --> 00:53:43,688
- What? What is it? - I don't know.

1448
00:53:43,689 --> 00:53:45,435
(A giant river spreads before the siblings!)

1449
00:53:45,459 --> 00:53:47,088
It's a yacht.

1450
00:53:47,089 --> 00:53:48,689
- Are we going to ride a yacht? - Yes.

1451
00:53:49,959 --> 00:53:52,028
(Is that a yacht?)

1452
00:53:52,029 --> 00:53:55,168
Why did you wrap your feet tightly with plastic sheets?

1453
00:53:55,169 --> 00:53:56,169
Exactly.

1454
00:53:56,469 --> 00:53:57,868
(The staff's boots grab their attention.)

1455
00:53:57,869 --> 00:53:59,739
We'll let you know once you get changed.

1456
00:54:00,439 --> 00:54:02,809
- Okay. - Why can't you tell us at once?

1457
00:54:03,339 --> 00:54:06,979
What on earth are we going to do?

1458
00:54:08,279 --> 00:54:09,779
Let's see.

1459
00:54:12,049 --> 00:54:17,489
(They wear the knee-high boots.)

1460
00:54:18,289 --> 00:54:19,688
(Everyone got changed.)

1461
00:54:19,689 --> 00:54:20,888
Let's go.

1462
00:54:20,889 --> 00:54:23,029
(Everyone got changed.)

1463
00:54:23,429 --> 00:54:26,028
Can you guess what you'll do?

1464
00:54:26,029 --> 00:54:27,258
- No. - Not at all.

1465
00:54:27,259 --> 00:54:28,429
Not at all. Seriously.

1466
00:54:28,729 --> 00:54:31,199
I see that there are many palm trees here.

1467
00:54:32,839 --> 00:54:34,738
Are we harvesting coconuts?

1468
00:54:34,739 --> 00:54:35,739
(Coconuts?)

1469
00:54:37,239 --> 00:54:40,479
(Thick palm trees along the river)

1470
00:54:43,979 --> 00:54:44,979
Durian?

1471
00:54:45,349 --> 00:54:47,248
It could be durian.

1472
00:54:47,249 --> 00:54:49,048
I think we'll be picking fruits.

1473
00:54:49,049 --> 00:54:50,769
(Dex thinks they'll pick palm tree fruits.)

1474
00:54:50,989 --> 00:54:54,159
The first work you'll do in the Philippines...

1475
00:54:56,359 --> 00:54:59,029
is something even the locals have a hard time catching it.

1476
00:55:00,199 --> 00:55:02,669
The rare and expensive specialty of Bohol,

1477
00:55:03,869 --> 00:55:05,299
alimango.

1478
00:55:05,699 --> 00:55:07,939
- Alimango? - Alimango?

1479
00:55:08,198 --> 00:55:09,638
Alimango.

1480
00:55:10,068 --> 00:55:12,268
- Alimango? - Alimango?

1481
00:55:12,708 --> 00:55:13,837
What's that?

1482
00:55:13,838 --> 00:55:16,238
You said "catch," so it must be some kind of fish.

1483
00:55:16,678 --> 00:55:17,937
- Is it fish? - It's a type of crab.

1484
00:55:17,938 --> 00:55:18,978
Crab?

1485
00:55:21,748 --> 00:55:23,378
(It has huge claws.)

1486
00:55:25,318 --> 00:55:28,418
(The tyrant of the mudflats)

1487
00:55:30,658 --> 00:55:31,827
It won't let go at all.

1488
00:55:31,828 --> 00:55:33,668
(It doesn't let go once it pinches something.)

1489
00:55:34,998 --> 00:55:37,928
Catching alimango is very dangerous...

1490
00:55:38,398 --> 00:55:40,028
for the unskilled.

1491
00:55:40,568 --> 00:55:43,537
If things go wrong, you could hurt your hand badly.

1492
00:55:43,538 --> 00:55:45,658
(If things go wrong, you could hurt your hand badly.)

1493
00:55:46,608 --> 00:55:49,508
We normally catch 1 to 2.

1494
00:55:50,238 --> 00:55:52,548
Some days, we catch nothing.

1495
00:55:55,148 --> 00:55:57,748
About one kilogram of alimango...

1496
00:55:59,048 --> 00:56:01,117
can be sold at 700 pesos.

1497
00:56:01,118 --> 00:56:03,688
(700 pesos is around 17.5 dollars.)

1498
00:56:04,618 --> 00:56:06,387
(It's more expensive than a day's worth of minimum wage, )

1499
00:56:06,388 --> 00:56:08,158
(which is around 500 pesos.)

1500
00:56:09,058 --> 00:56:13,168
(Bohol's top-notch specialty)

1501
00:56:13,868 --> 00:56:15,537
(The 4 siblings' 1st mission)

1502
00:56:15,538 --> 00:56:17,198
(Catching alimango)

1503
00:56:17,868 --> 00:56:21,608
You'll travel by boat to get to work.

1504
00:56:22,178 --> 00:56:24,478
If the four of you...

1505
00:56:25,048 --> 00:56:28,118
catch 4 alimangos in total, I'll give you 1 coin.

1506
00:56:28,278 --> 00:56:29,278
Four?

1507
00:56:29,279 --> 00:56:32,587
You're adding all our crabs, right? Not counting individually?

1508
00:56:32,588 --> 00:56:36,988
And for every two alimangos you catch after that,

1509
00:56:37,188 --> 00:56:40,088
we'll give you one coin.

1510
00:56:40,658 --> 00:56:43,657
Using the coins,

1511
00:56:43,658 --> 00:56:45,967
- you can fill up your schedule. - That's nice.

1512
00:56:45,968 --> 00:56:47,767
It must be very hard to catch it.

1513
00:56:47,768 --> 00:56:50,338
- We get a coin for catching 1. - A coin for 4 crabs.

1514
00:56:52,868 --> 00:56:54,038
I want to go home.

1515
00:56:55,508 --> 00:56:56,607
(Are you okay?)

1516
00:56:56,608 --> 00:56:58,208
(No.)

1517
00:56:59,808 --> 00:57:02,518
(It's not harvesting, it's surviving.)

1518
00:57:03,018 --> 00:57:04,477
(A beast's...)

1519
00:57:04,478 --> 00:57:06,147
(feces?)

1520
00:57:06,148 --> 00:57:07,317
It's huge.

1521
00:57:07,318 --> 00:57:09,587
- It went in. - Over there. It went in.

1522
00:57:09,588 --> 00:57:12,058
(What happened to the four siblings?)

1523
00:57:13,328 --> 00:57:16,227
(They set sail at 7:45am.)

1524
00:57:16,228 --> 00:57:19,297
If it's 1 coin for 4 crabs...

1525
00:57:19,298 --> 00:57:21,668
- Is it that hard to catch one? - I wonder too.

1526
00:57:25,908 --> 00:57:29,978
(They wear their protective gears, cut-resistant gloves.)

1527
00:57:30,808 --> 00:57:33,848
(Half-excited, half-nervous)

1528
00:57:34,578 --> 00:57:36,748
(The youngest in particular is very nervous.)

1529
00:57:37,148 --> 00:57:39,687
(Glancing)

1530
00:57:39,688 --> 00:57:41,188
Hye Yoon. Here.

1531
00:57:41,348 --> 00:57:43,988
Your eyelash.

1532
00:57:45,888 --> 00:57:47,627
Hair... It's an eyelash.

1533
00:57:47,628 --> 00:57:49,188
(Spotting an eyelash stuck on her face)

1534
00:57:49,758 --> 00:57:51,428
- It flew away. - It's gone.

1535
00:57:52,528 --> 00:57:54,028
An eyelash?

1536
00:57:54,328 --> 00:57:56,968
- You're detailed. - Since you're an actress and all.

1537
00:57:57,438 --> 00:57:58,707
He's attentive.

1538
00:57:58,708 --> 00:58:00,968
(Her nervousness melts away a little.)

1539
00:58:01,638 --> 00:58:02,778
Don't be so happy about it.

1540
00:58:03,708 --> 00:58:05,828
- What's with him? - You better catch a lot of crabs.

1541
00:58:06,708 --> 00:58:08,008
What's wrong with him?

1542
00:58:09,778 --> 00:58:11,418
The weather is so nice.

1543
00:58:11,888 --> 00:58:14,517
It's really nice if you don't think about work.

1544
00:58:14,518 --> 00:58:15,918
Look. It's stunning.

1545
00:58:18,588 --> 00:58:22,028
Now that I'm in the shade, the sky is so pretty.

1546
00:58:23,128 --> 00:58:25,028
So is the grass.

1547
00:58:27,198 --> 00:58:29,668
It's fantastic if you don't think about the upcoming labor.

1548
00:58:30,168 --> 00:58:32,208
I'm so happy. It's relaxing.

1549
00:58:33,738 --> 00:58:36,408
- It's so pretty. - It's so cool.

1550
00:58:37,078 --> 00:58:38,347
It is pretty cool.

1551
00:58:38,348 --> 00:58:40,277
- It's so pretty. - The sea.

1552
00:58:40,278 --> 00:58:41,917
(The four siblings sail across the raw nature.)

1553
00:58:41,918 --> 00:58:43,678
Aren't we going a bit too far?

1554
00:58:43,848 --> 00:58:45,118
- I know, right? - Yes.

1555
00:58:49,388 --> 00:58:51,858
(15 minutes since they set sail)

1556
00:58:53,158 --> 00:58:55,028
