It is there, right? Do you feel it?

1823
01:11:52,438 --> 01:11:54,608
There is something hard.

1824
01:11:55,538 --> 01:11:56,577
But this...

1825
01:11:56,578 --> 01:11:58,238
(He's not confident.)

1826
01:11:58,738 --> 01:12:01,377
(Jung Ah goes next.)

1827
01:12:01,378 --> 01:12:02,478
I can't feel anything.

1828
01:12:03,378 --> 01:12:04,748
- Put yours in. - Let me try too.

1829
01:12:06,248 --> 01:12:07,948
Do you feel something hard?

1830
01:12:08,918 --> 01:12:09,958
Hard?

1831
01:12:10,358 --> 01:12:11,888
There isn't anything, right?

1832
01:12:12,788 --> 01:12:15,698
No. It doesn't feel any different from a tree.

1833
01:12:16,358 --> 01:12:17,898
The hook is touching nothing.

1834
01:12:19,968 --> 01:12:23,668
(Jassel tries instead.)

1835
01:12:24,098 --> 01:12:26,237
(Frustrated)

1836
01:12:26,238 --> 01:12:27,438
You can't tell at all.

1837
01:12:29,838 --> 01:12:31,708
(Surprised)

1838
01:12:33,578 --> 01:12:34,978
There was something.

1839
01:12:35,078 --> 01:12:37,518
(There was an alimango!)

1840
01:12:38,048 --> 01:12:40,088
(It was there, and we couldn't feel it?)

1841
01:12:40,188 --> 01:12:42,717
- How are we supposed to catch it? - Exactly. How can we do this?

1842
01:12:42,718 --> 01:12:44,798
I guess it's true they can catch only a few per day.

1843
01:12:45,318 --> 01:12:47,058
It'll be hard to find one.

1844
01:12:47,088 --> 01:12:49,297
It's not one of those crabs which you can catch a lot.

1845
01:12:49,298 --> 01:12:51,178
(They need to catch 4 like this to get 1 coin.)

1846
01:12:52,358 --> 01:12:53,798
Where is Jun Myun?

1847
01:12:53,968 --> 01:12:55,267
My question exactly. She's disappeared.

1848
01:12:55,268 --> 01:12:57,038
I think she's gone back to the boat.

1849
01:12:57,498 --> 01:12:59,108
She must be on the boat.

1850
01:12:59,208 --> 01:13:00,938
Seriously...

1851
01:13:01,568 --> 01:13:02,578
Where...

1852
01:13:02,608 --> 01:13:04,577
Did Jun Myun disappear?

1853
01:13:04,578 --> 01:13:05,607
Exactly.

1854
01:13:05,608 --> 01:13:06,708
Where is she?

1855
01:13:07,308 --> 01:13:08,848
What's happening?

1856
01:13:10,918 --> 01:13:14,548
(She acquires what used to be a palm fruit.)

1857
01:13:14,788 --> 01:13:17,488
I'll catch just one and go.

1858
01:13:18,488 --> 01:13:19,957
That's all we hope for too.

1859
01:13:19,958 --> 01:13:21,958
- Please. - Only one.

1860
01:13:22,188 --> 01:13:23,198
I want only one.

1861
01:13:23,228 --> 01:13:24,357
- Only one? - Yes.

1862
01:13:24,358 --> 01:13:25,798
- Yes, let's move forward. - Okay?

1863
01:13:26,528 --> 01:13:27,528
Let's go.

1864
01:13:29,098 --> 01:13:30,498
Let's keep moving forward.

1865
01:13:30,938 --> 01:13:32,098
Deep?

1866
01:13:32,198 --> 01:13:34,608
Yes, let's check all the holes here.

1867
01:13:34,908 --> 01:13:37,407
If you can see a crab hole...

1868
01:13:37,408 --> 01:13:39,378
The crab is not easy to find.

1869
01:13:40,078 --> 01:13:43,448
That's why you just need to work hard to get one.

1870
01:13:44,118 --> 01:13:46,718
(Jun Myun is paired with a strict partner.)

1871
01:13:47,048 --> 01:13:48,048
Goodness.

1872
01:13:49,558 --> 01:13:53,158
Gosh. There's that saying, right?

1873
01:13:53,858 --> 01:13:55,628
"Looking for a Mr. Kim in Hanyang."

1874
01:13:55,728 --> 01:13:58,598
(Laughing)

1875
01:14:01,998 --> 01:14:05,638
Where on earth are the crabs in these holes?

1876
01:14:07,438 --> 01:14:08,467
Gosh, I'm exhausted.

1877
01:14:08,468 --> 01:14:09,477
(Looking for Mr. Crab...)

1878
01:14:09,478 --> 01:14:11,438
(It's been 40 minutes.)

1879
01:14:13,508 --> 01:14:16,417
I mean, really.

1880
01:14:16,418 --> 01:14:18,058
(I mean, really. There aren't any crabs.)

1881
01:14:18,718 --> 01:14:20,788
I think there's nothing.

1882
01:14:23,088 --> 01:14:26,128
Maybe there was high tide last night.

1883
01:14:26,658 --> 01:14:29,357
They make another hole...

1884
01:14:29,358 --> 01:14:31,058
or go out and find some food.

1885
01:14:34,328 --> 01:14:35,938
I see.

1886
01:14:37,598 --> 01:14:38,878
Please let me feel the hardness.

1887
01:14:41,008 --> 01:14:42,037
Please let me feel the hardness.

1888
01:14:42,038 --> 01:14:44,078
(He keeps hoping to strike the hardness of a crab.)

1889
01:14:44,138 --> 01:14:46,178
(Gosh)

1890
01:14:46,848 --> 01:14:48,008
I don't feel anything.

1891
01:14:48,348 --> 01:14:50,418
- No crab. - No crab.

1892
01:14:50,818 --> 01:14:52,588
No hardness, no crab.

1893
01:14:54,348 --> 01:14:55,417
(Did he feel the hardness of a crab this time?)

1894
01:14:55,418 --> 01:14:56,687
Gosh, no.

1895
01:14:56,688 --> 01:14:58,518
(No hardness)

1896
01:14:59,058 --> 01:15:01,628
(He keeps digging and digging.)

1897
01:15:01,658 --> 01:15:02,728
No hardness.

1898
01:15:04,658 --> 01:15:06,067
No hardness!

1899
01:15:06,068 --> 01:15:07,527
- Did you find one? - No crab.

1900
01:15:07,528 --> 01:15:08,904
(The "No hardness, no crab" streak continues.)

1901
01:15:08,928 --> 01:15:11,838
Who on earth came all the way here and caught crabs?

1902
01:15:11,938 --> 01:15:13,907
Who started it? Why?

1903
01:15:13,908 --> 01:15:15,828
(They've begun to raise a fundamental question.)

1904
01:15:16,038 --> 01:15:19,077
I thought I'd be able to catch at least one.

1905
01:15:19,078 --> 01:15:20,424
(It's as if she had suddenly possessed.)

1906
01:15:20,448 --> 01:15:21,678
I haven't found any.

1907
01:15:22,748 --> 01:15:25,148
I feel like I'm starting to forget what crabs look like.

1908
01:15:25,418 --> 01:15:26,788
Were the crabs hard?

1909
01:15:31,088 --> 01:15:33,328
Where are you, crabs?

1910
01:15:34,958 --> 01:15:36,028
Gosh, I feel dizzy.

1911
01:15:36,758 --> 01:15:39,528
(She's already covered in mud.)

1912
01:15:39,968 --> 01:15:42,128
- Are you okay? - No.

1913
01:15:43,238 --> 01:15:45,038
I thought this was supposed to be a vacation.

1914
01:15:45,238 --> 01:15:47,307
Are you sure this is a vacation?

1915
01:15:47,308 --> 01:15:48,868
(This is practically employment fraud.)

1916
01:15:50,638 --> 01:15:51,878
I want to go home.

1917
01:15:52,438 --> 01:15:54,424
(Once you leave home, it's nothing but crab-level suffering.)

1918
01:15:54,448 --> 01:15:56,318
How is this a vacation?

1919
01:15:57,948 --> 01:15:59,178
This isn't it at all.

1920
01:16:01,188 --> 01:16:05,018
(They must earn coins to enjoy their vacation.)

1921
01:16:06,058 --> 01:16:08,558
I don't think we'll be able to find four crabs.

1922
01:16:09,698 --> 01:16:11,157
This is really draining my energy.

1923
01:16:11,158 --> 01:16:13,238
(It's been an hour since the alimango hunt started.)

1924
01:16:13,868 --> 01:16:14,868
Gosh.

1925
01:16:17,868 --> 01:16:19,568
There aren't any crabs.

1926
01:16:19,668 --> 01:16:21,338
(Laughing)

1927
01:16:21,638 --> 01:16:23,907
(Jun Myun has completely lost it.)

1928
01:16:23,908 --> 01:16:24,908
(Laughing)
Darn it.

1929
01:16:27,708 --> 01:16:29,448
(Gosh...)

1930
01:16:30,618 --> 01:16:32,077
(She pulls herself together and resumes the search.)

1931
01:16:32,078 --> 01:16:33,088
(Snorting)

1932
01:16:33,188 --> 01:16:35,347
(Laughing)

1933
01:16:35,348 --> 01:16:36,488
There aren't any crabs!

1934
01:16:39,058 --> 01:16:41,557
- What's your name? - Howey.

1935
01:16:41,558 --> 01:16:44,258
So, how're we doing this, Howey?

1936
01:16:44,958 --> 01:16:46,097
All right. Hole.

1937
01:16:46,098 --> 01:16:49,128
If you're lucky, like...

1938
01:16:49,598 --> 01:16:50,897
- I see. - Yes.

1939
01:16:50,898 --> 01:16:52,298
- The sound? - Yes.

1940
01:16:53,008 --> 01:16:54,607
It means that there's a crab inside.

1941
01:16:54,608 --> 01:16:55,608
How old are you?

1942
01:16:55,609 --> 01:16:57,137
- I'm 24. - You're 24?

1943
01:16:57,138 --> 01:16:58,178
- Yes. - Okay.

1944
01:16:58,708 --> 01:17:00,677
(Laughing)

1945
01:17:00,678 --> 01:17:03,218
Find some holes there and see...

1946
01:17:03,718 --> 01:17:05,447
- some crabs, because... - Howey.

1947
01:17:05,448 --> 01:17:06,618
- Yes? - Okay.

1948
01:17:06,818 --> 01:17:10,457
I know you explain. Okay, I got it.

1949
01:17:10,458 --> 01:17:12,418
I understand, but...

1950
01:17:13,528 --> 01:17:14,888
it's very, very hard.

1951
01:17:14,988 --> 01:17:17,028
That's why I... You got this!

1952
01:17:18,298 --> 01:17:19,328
You got this!

1953
01:17:20,698 --> 01:17:22,267
This one is...

1954
01:17:22,268 --> 01:17:23,597
Try to find other holes.

1955
01:17:23,598 --> 01:17:24,598
(Threatening mode on)

1956
01:17:24,599 --> 01:17:25,898
Yes, you got this.

1957
01:17:27,538 --> 01:17:30,018
The way he's smiling as he says "You got this" is so annoying.

1958
01:17:30,108 --> 01:17:32,538
Okay. Howey, you're 25? Okay.

1959
01:17:33,008 --> 01:17:35,848
Okay.

1960
01:17:35,948 --> 01:17:38,748
(Confucian values don't really work in the Philippines.)

1961
01:17:39,218 --> 01:17:40,458
We've already checked that one.

1962
01:17:41,448 --> 01:17:42,818
(Gosh)

1963
01:17:44,688 --> 01:17:45,688
(The sound of Jun Myun hitting something solid)
I heard the sound.

1964
01:17:49,458 --> 01:17:51,928
(She clearly heard a dull thud.)

1965
01:17:52,328 --> 01:17:53,968
- I heard a sound. - You heard the sound?

1966
01:17:54,268 --> 01:17:56,148
(The sound of Jun Myun hitting something solid)

1967
01:17:56,338 --> 01:17:57,978
- I heard a sound. - You heard the sound?

1968
01:18:00,568 --> 01:18:02,808
(She scratched the surface of something.)

1969
01:18:04,778 --> 01:18:05,807
Wait.

1970
01:18:05,808 --> 01:18:07,508
(Jun Myun keeps digging.)

1971
01:18:08,578 --> 01:18:11,518
I think there's a crab shell here.

1972
01:18:20,088 --> 01:18:21,488
I have no energy left.

1973
01:18:21,588 --> 01:18:23,728
I caught one!

1974
01:18:25,858 --> 01:18:27,368
I have no energy left.

1975
01:18:27,468 --> 01:18:29,638
I caught one!

1976
01:18:31,198 --> 01:18:33,968
(A crab's claw comes into view.)

1977
01:18:34,368 --> 01:18:36,808
Gosh. I caught one.

1978
01:18:37,238 --> 01:18:38,238
I caught one.

1979
01:18:38,239 --> 01:18:39,848
(The battle with the crab has begun.)

1980
01:18:40,648 --> 01:18:42,448
- No, don't touch. - No. Okay.

1981
01:18:43,618 --> 01:18:45,277
(In a rush, Jun Myun reached out.)

1982
01:18:45,278 --> 01:18:46,318
I caught one.

1983
01:18:50,088 --> 01:18:52,218
Okay. It's clamping down hard too.

1984
01:18:52,518 --> 01:18:53,587
I caught one.

1985
01:18:53,588 --> 01:18:56,068
(It's a full-on tug-of-war between Jun Myun and the alimango.)

1986
01:18:57,628 --> 01:18:58,628
No!

1987
01:18:59,328 --> 01:19:01,668
(Gripping tightly)

1988
01:19:02,268 --> 01:19:03,798
Grab it. Yes, you grab onto it.

1989
01:19:07,038 --> 01:19:08,438
(Shouting)

1990
01:19:10,408 --> 01:19:11,408
Goodness.

1991
01:19:15,048 --> 01:19:17,178
I only got a leg.

1992
01:19:18,478 --> 01:19:19,688
(Dropping his head)

1993
01:19:20,118 --> 01:19:22,248
That means the body is still in there.

1994
01:19:22,348 --> 01:19:25,818
It will bite it very, very strong.

1995
01:19:26,458 --> 01:19:28,657
But the claw, it shifts.

1996
01:19:28,658 --> 01:19:29,658
(The claw won't release.)

1997
01:19:29,958 --> 01:19:31,097
(Please don't run away.)

1998
01:19:31,098 --> 01:19:32,827
Because it's strong enough.

1999
01:19:32,828 --> 01:19:36,637
(Don't run away. I'll get you.)

2000
01:19:36,638 --> 01:19:37,668
I need the crab whole.

2001
01:19:41,808 --> 01:19:42,808
(The sound of Jun Myun hitting something solid)

2002
01:19:42,809 --> 01:19:44,178
It's here.

2003
01:19:47,548 --> 01:19:50,018
(The crab's body came into view.)

2004
01:19:53,188 --> 01:19:55,117
Gosh, it's so big.

2005
01:19:55,118 --> 01:19:56,798
(Here comes the 4 siblings' 1st alimango.)

2006
01:19:57,158 --> 01:19:59,257
Gosh, it's so big.

2007
01:19:59,258 --> 01:20:01,057
(Screaming)

2008
01:20:01,058 --> 01:20:02,058
(Shrieking)

2009
01:20:02,658 --> 01:20:03,658
(Shouting)

2010
01:20:04,258 --> 01:20:06,098
(Screaming)

2011
01:20:06,298 --> 01:20:07,298
(Shrieking)

2012
01:20:07,498 --> 01:20:08,498
Did she catch one?

2013
01:20:08,728 --> 01:20:10,668
Gosh, no.

2014
01:20:11,168 --> 01:20:12,238
I think she caught one.

2015
01:20:13,568 --> 01:20:15,737
I hear screaming. It must be good news, right?

2016
01:20:15,738 --> 01:20:17,808
Nice.

2017
01:20:17,908 --> 01:20:20,578
It came out. No.

2018
01:20:22,078 --> 01:20:25,948
(The crab is trying to hide.)

2019
01:20:27,218 --> 01:20:29,688
(With cut-resistant gloves on, she bravely grabs the crab.)

2020
01:20:30,858 --> 01:20:32,617
Goodness.

2021
01:20:32,618 --> 01:20:33,938
(She plucked it from the ground!)

2022
01:20:35,228 --> 01:20:37,458
Goodness.

2023
01:20:38,158 --> 01:20:39,198
I'm going home.

2024
01:20:40,468 --> 01:20:42,327
I did it. Okay.

2025
01:20:42,328 --> 01:20:43,338
Yes.

2026
01:20:44,698 --> 01:20:49,638
(Jassel's crab, Jun Myun's crab)

2027
01:20:49,908 --> 01:20:51,207
- Am I the first one? - Yes.

2028
01:20:51,208 --> 01:20:52,908
Yes, I came in first.

2029
01:20:53,578 --> 01:20:55,648
Gosh. Jun Myun's amazing.

2030
01:20:56,108 --> 01:20:57,318
She kept her promise.

2031
01:20:58,278 --> 01:20:59,818
She said she'd catch at least one.

2032
01:21:02,148 --> 01:21:04,488
What if I end up not catching any, myself?

2033
01:21:06,688 --> 01:21:08,428
No hardness!

2034
01:21:10,098 --> 01:21:12,598
I can't feel the hardness anywhere.

2035
01:21:13,368 --> 01:21:14,468
How did she do it?

2036
01:21:15,028 --> 01:21:18,438
Gosh, who knew catching crabs would be this difficult?

2037
01:21:18,938 --> 01:21:19,938
This is driving me insane.

2038
01:21:19,939 --> 01:21:21,179
(Hye Yoon has fully gone dark.)

2039
01:21:21,708 --> 01:21:25,378
Gosh. I feel lightheaded. Excuse me.

2040
01:21:26,178 --> 01:21:27,248
There aren't any crabs.

2041
01:21:29,578 --> 01:21:31,647
(Leader Yum is completely drained too.)

2042
01:21:31,648 --> 01:21:32,718
Gosh, I feel dizzy.

2043
01:21:33,688 --> 01:21:35,187
Jun Myun, did you find one? Did you catch it?

2044
01:21:35,188 --> 01:21:36,257
Yes, I caught one.

2045
01:21:36,258 --> 01:21:37,258
- You caught one? - Yes.

2046
01:21:37,259 --> 01:21:39,088
- That's amazing. - It was huge.

2047
01:21:39,188 --> 01:21:40,227
Goodness.

2048
01:21:40,228 --> 01:21:41,457
Come and see what I caught.

2049
01:21:41,458 --> 01:21:42,588
Look.

2050
01:21:42,888 --> 01:21:44,458
- That's huge. - Right? It's huge.

2051
01:21:45,628 --> 01:21:47,067
(Feeling wronged)

2052
01:21:47,068 --> 01:21:48,128
I've been...

2053
01:21:48,798 --> 01:21:50,697
- The crab shells that we eat. - Yes.

2054
01:21:50,698 --> 01:21:52,938
I felt that.

2055
01:21:53,668 --> 01:21:55,307
- I pulled it up and it was a crab. - I haven't felt that.

2056
01:21:55,308 --> 01:21:56,607
(The confidence of someone who already caught a crab)

2057
01:21:56,608 --> 01:21:58,288
You should try again after taking a break.

2058
01:21:58,638 --> 01:22:00,947
I honestly want to leave since I caught one,

2059
01:22:00,948 --> 01:22:02,177
- but I'm staying out of loyalty. - All right.

2060
01:22:02,178 --> 01:22:04,378
Yes, you've got the right attitude.

2061
01:22:07,948 --> 01:22:09,247
(I should catch one too.)

2062
01:22:09,248 --> 01:22:10,368
There's nothing around here.

2063
01:22:11,188 --> 01:22:12,887
(Turning toward Jassel)

2064
01:22:12,888 --> 01:22:13,928
What's your name?

2065
01:22:14,088 --> 01:22:16,398
- Jassel. - What?

2066
01:22:16,698 --> 01:22:18,728
- Jassel? - Yes, Jassel.

2067
01:22:18,828 --> 01:22:20,127
- Jassel. - Jassel.

2068
01:22:20,128 --> 01:22:21,128
The hardness.

2069
01:22:21,468 --> 01:22:22,868
- You caught one? - You caught one?

2070
01:22:23,868 --> 01:22:24,868
What?

2071
01:22:26,838 --> 01:22:28,137
Is this the hardness? Yes.

2072
01:22:28,138 --> 01:22:29,138
(Talking to himself)

2073
01:22:30,938 --> 01:22:33,048
(He feels the hardness?)

2074
01:22:33,508 --> 01:22:35,777
It's hard. The hardness!

2075
01:22:35,778 --> 01:22:38,548
(It's definitely hard!)

2076
01:22:38,678 --> 01:22:39,687
- You caught one? - You caught one?

2077
01:22:39,688 --> 01:22:40,688
No.

2078
01:22:41,088 --> 01:22:42,888
Gosh, he just has a loud voice.

2079
01:22:44,158 --> 01:22:46,058
(Listen carefully to the sound.)

2080
01:22:47,558 --> 01:22:48,628
This sound.

2081
01:22:49,658 --> 01:22:51,998
(That's clearly the sound of something hard being struck.)

2082
01:22:52,998 --> 01:22:55,428
(The hardness he's been searching for)

2083
01:22:56,638 --> 01:22:58,237
I really think there's something here.

2084
01:22:58,238 --> 01:22:59,358
(Is it really the hardness?)

2085
01:23:02,638 --> 01:23:03,638
Gosh.

2086
01:23:03,639 --> 01:23:06,208
(But...)

2087
01:23:06,948 --> 01:23:09,348
(only a claw came up, just like what happened to Jun Myun.)

2088
01:23:09,918 --> 01:23:13,047
It broke.

2089
01:23:13,048 --> 01:23:14,728
(That means the alimango could be inside.)

2090
01:23:15,088 --> 01:23:16,088
It's inside.

2091
01:23:19,858 --> 01:23:21,758
Gosh, it's coming up.

2092
01:23:23,598 --> 01:23:26,258
(Crab legs emerge.)

2093
01:23:26,768 --> 01:23:27,827
Do not touch.

2094
01:23:27,828 --> 01:23:29,004
(Dex reaches out without thinking too.)

2095
01:23:29,028 --> 01:23:32,438
(Screaming)

2096
01:23:33,138 --> 01:23:36,538
(Hold it right there!)

2097
01:23:36,738 --> 01:23:39,207
Yes, I know.

2098
01:23:39,208 --> 01:23:41,708
(He caught it!)

2099
01:23:49,918 --> 01:23:50,958
I caught it!

2100
01:23:51,418 --> 01:23:52,657
- He caught one! - I caught it!

2101
01:23:52,658 --> 01:23:53,728
You caught one?

2102
01:23:53,928 --> 01:23:56,028
It's okay.

2103
01:23:56,498 --> 01:24:00,398
(Come here, alimango.)

2104
01:24:01,968 --> 01:24:04,798
(It's extra-large.)

2105
01:24:05,268 --> 01:24:07,007
(Laughing)

2106
01:24:07,008 --> 01:24:08,067
(He caught an alimango with a hard shell.)

2107
01:24:08,068 --> 01:24:09,108
I caught one.

2108
01:24:09,338 --> 01:24:11,437
- Jin Young, how many did you catch? - I caught one.

2109
01:24:11,438 --> 01:24:12,654
(Currently, there are a total of 2.)

2110
01:24:12,678 --> 01:24:15,348
What? Everyone's catching crabs except me.

2111
01:24:18,318 --> 01:24:19,747
It's really huge.

2112
01:24:19,748 --> 01:24:21,348
(I didn't catch one, either.)

2113
01:24:21,888 --> 01:24:22,947
This is fun.

2114
01:24:22,948 --> 01:24:24,658
(Laughing)

2115
01:24:25,018 --> 01:24:27,128
Do they have clams here too?

2116
01:24:28,388 --> 01:24:30,068
I'm glad at least one of us is having fun.

2117
01:24:30,458 --> 01:24:32,028
Dex says he's having fun.

2118
01:24:36,538 --> 01:24:41,608
(She doesn't seem to be having much fun.)

2119
01:24:42,068 --> 01:24:44,338
- Jung Ah, start by knocking. - Knocking?

2120
01:24:44,978 --> 01:24:46,418
I can't go randomly knocking around.

2121
01:24:47,648 --> 01:24:49,607
(I could pass out.)

2122
01:24:49,608 --> 01:24:50,778
This isn't an easy task.

2123
01:24:52,078 --> 01:24:54,117
We have 2 now. We only need 2 more.

2124
01:24:54,118 --> 01:24:55,347
(They're 1 hour and 40 minutes into the alimango hunt.)

2125
01:24:55,348 --> 01:24:57,758
- Catch 2 more? - Yes, just 2 more.

2126
01:24:59,718 --> 01:25:00,758
Okay.

2127
01:25:01,658 --> 01:25:04,598
Okay. I think I now have an idea of what the crab holes look like.

2128
01:25:05,728 --> 01:25:07,068
I need more crabs.

2129
01:25:07,328 --> 01:25:09,028
(He has a crazed look in his eyes.)

2130
01:25:09,968 --> 01:25:11,837
(I'll get us the coin we need to change our schedule.)

2131
01:25:11,838 --> 01:25:13,098
I need to find a big hole.

2132
01:25:19,108 --> 01:25:20,948
I think I can catch one here.

2133
01:25:23,218 --> 01:25:24,717
I think this is it.

2134
01:25:24,718 --> 01:25:25,948
(Did he find a crab hole?)

2135
01:25:28,218 --> 01:25:30,618
(What?)

2136
01:25:30,988 --> 01:25:32,658
- Do you feel it? - Yes, I feel it.

2137
01:25:33,428 --> 01:25:34,588
I feel the hardness.

2138
01:25:36,458 --> 01:25:37,528
Gosh, I feel it.

2139
01:25:37,798 --> 01:25:39,028
Over there.

2140
01:25:39,628 --> 01:25:40,698
Did you find one?

2141
01:25:42,768 --> 01:25:43,998
Dex caught one.

2142
01:25:45,068 --> 01:25:47,208
Dex is amazing, as expected.

2143
01:25:48,168 --> 01:25:50,108
How is he so good at this?

2144
01:25:51,138 --> 01:25:52,608
Jin Young is on a roll.

2145
01:25:53,108 --> 01:25:56,347
Once I find a hole, catching the crab isn't that hard.

2146
01:25:56,348 --> 01:26:00,318
(Only 1 more crab to catch to earn 1 coin.)

2147
01:26:01,018 --> 01:26:03,988
If I could recognize the crab holes, I'd be able to do something.

2148
01:26:06,158 --> 01:26:07,327
This isn't it.

2149
01:26:07,328 --> 01:26:09,088
Hye Yoon, did you catch one?

2150
01:26:09,658 --> 01:26:10,897
No, I didn't.

2151
01:26:10,898 --> 01:26:12,057
(Crying)

2152
01:26:12,058 --> 01:26:13,598
This isn't easy to do.

2153
01:26:14,068 --> 01:26:15,098
It really isn't.

2154
01:26:15,228 --> 01:26:17,398
If I catch one, we'll be done here.

2155
01:26:18,668 --> 01:26:21,008
(They're only 1 crab away from earning 1 coin.)

2156
01:26:21,338 --> 01:26:23,978
(I'll catch one, no matter what!)

2157
01:26:28,778 --> 01:26:32,148
(Please let me catch one!)

2158
01:26:32,618 --> 01:26:33,688
Nothing.

2159
01:26:35,148 --> 01:26:37,017
(That alimango...)

2160
01:26:37,018 --> 01:26:39,718
(How badly I want to catch one...)

2161
01:26:40,488 --> 01:26:44,128
Goodness, let's move on.

2162
01:26:44,258 --> 01:26:46,328
(Please let this be it.)

2163
01:26:48,768 --> 01:26:53,338
(Jung Ah has been digging and digging for crab holes.)

2164
01:26:54,308 --> 01:26:56,838
(But there aren't any crabs in sight.)

2165
01:26:57,078 --> 01:26:58,378
I don't have power.

2166
01:26:59,578 --> 01:27:02,778
(Alimango, where on earth are you?)

2167
01:27:03,478 --> 01:27:07,587
This wouldn't be that hard, if it weren't for the mud.

2168
01:27:07,588 --> 01:27:08,988
The mud is what makes it difficult.

2169
01:27:09,188 --> 01:27:10,748
No, the fact that I haven't caught any.

2170
01:27:12,088 --> 01:27:13,587
(Leader Yum is more sorry that she isn't helping...)

2171
01:27:13,588 --> 01:27:15,088
(than she is exhausted.)

2172
01:27:15,658 --> 01:27:17,558
(Worried)

2173
01:27:17,758 --> 01:27:19,698
Jung Ah, do whatever you can to catch one.

2174
01:27:20,398 --> 01:27:22,427
Please, one more. Please.

2175
01:27:22,428 --> 01:27:24,068
(That's right. I'm Yum Jung Ah.)

2176
01:27:24,968 --> 01:27:27,168
(Even when I was getting hit with anchovies, )

2177
01:27:28,068 --> 01:27:30,908
(even when I was shoveling through 28 tons of water laver, )

2178
01:27:31,708 --> 01:27:34,878
(there was no such thing as giving up in my dictionary.)

2179
01:27:35,648 --> 01:27:37,848
(I will never give up this time, either.)

2180
01:27:38,118 --> 01:27:39,178
One!

2181
01:27:39,578 --> 01:27:41,687
(Stop right there, alimango.)

2182
01:27:41,688 --> 01:27:43,618
(I'm on my way to catch you!)

2183
01:27:44,018 --> 01:27:46,117
(Jun Myun follows Jung Ah.)

2184
01:27:46,118 --> 01:27:48,657
(Stumble)

2185
01:27:48,658 --> 01:27:50,858
- Be careful. - I keep falling here.

2186
01:27:56,368 --> 01:27:58,728
(Since she's stuck there anyway, she begins raking around.)

2187
01:27:59,438 --> 01:28:00,507
I'm checking the water vein.

2188
01:28:00,508 --> 01:28:01,537
(Embarrassed)

2189
01:28:01,538 --> 01:28:02,938
Trying to feel the hardness.

2190
01:28:05,378 --> 01:28:08,248
(Meanwhile, Leader Yum goes through the muddy path.)

2191
01:28:08,478 --> 01:28:10,217
This is a jungle.

2192
01:28:10,218 --> 01:28:11,894
(She keeps walking toward an even deeper part of the jungle.)

2193
01:28:11,918 --> 01:28:14,088
(Let's see.)

2194
01:28:14,288 --> 01:28:16,618
(Jung Ah quickly looks around for crab holes.)

2195
01:28:18,058 --> 01:28:19,118
Let me poke around.

2196
01:28:20,888 --> 01:28:23,227
(I'm going to catch one this time. No matter what.)

2197
01:28:23,228 --> 01:28:25,528
(All I need is one crab!)

2198
01:28:30,038 --> 01:28:31,568
(What?)

2199
01:28:33,438 --> 01:28:38,138
(Does it feel like an alimango is approaching?)

2200
01:28:38,943 --> 01:28:40,183
(What?)

2201
01:28:40,313 --> 01:28:41,482
- Over there! - That's huge!

2202
01:28:41,483 --> 01:28:42,553
Gosh!

2203
01:28:43,113 --> 01:28:45,052
(The last battle)

2204
01:28:45,053 --> 01:28:46,053
(Shouting)

2205
01:28:46,353 --> 01:28:47,823
(No, the crabs are running away!)

2206
01:28:48,053 --> 01:28:49,493
(We only need one crab.)

2207
01:28:50,163 --> 01:28:52,122
(We must turn our schedule full of hellish labor...)

2208
01:28:52,123 --> 01:28:54,692
(into a vacation.)

2209
01:28:54,693 --> 01:28:56,033
(Help us.)

2210
01:28:56,933 --> 01:28:58,502
(Right now, )

2211
01:28:58,503 --> 01:29:01,433
(we need coins.)

2212
01:29:01,733 --> 01:29:03,502
(Those annoying coins)

2213
01:29:03,503 --> 01:29:05,473
(We'll win them by playing games.)

2214
01:29:05,773 --> 01:29:07,442
(Let's play.)

2215
01:29:07,443 --> 01:29:08,443
(Spitting)

2216
01:29:08,713 --> 01:29:09,713
What?
(Spitting)

2217
01:29:12,113 --> 01:29:14,429
(She was told to play the game, but Hye Yoon is spitting out saliva.)

2218
01:29:14,453 --> 01:29:16,353
(And Jun Myun got it?)

2219
01:29:16,823 --> 01:29:19,322
(I can't believe...)

2220
01:29:19,323 --> 01:29:21,253
(this actually worked.)

2221
01:29:22,523 --> 01:29:24,593
(Gosh, we're good at this.)

2222
01:29:24,693 --> 01:29:27,033
(A deity of games has joined the siblings.)

2223
01:29:27,433 --> 01:29:28,992
(Just shaking it...)

2224
01:29:28,993 --> 01:29:31,062
(triggers it.)

2225
01:29:31,063 --> 01:29:33,772
(Just shaking it...)

2226
01:29:33,773 --> 01:29:35,433
(triggers it.)

2227
01:29:35,703 --> 01:29:36,873
(What?)

2228
01:29:37,173 --> 01:29:39,243
(Did they just hit the jackpot?)

2229
01:29:39,603 --> 01:29:40,613
(Let's just use it.)

2230
01:29:40,973 --> 01:29:42,813
(Let's eat everything they recommend.)

2231
01:29:43,243 --> 01:29:45,683
(Should we eat everything that the Philippines has to offer?)

2232
01:29:45,883 --> 01:29:48,383
(A nonstop wave of...)

2233
01:29:48,853 --> 01:29:49,853
(Filipino local dishes)

2234
01:29:49,953 --> 01:29:51,922
(This is it.)

2235
01:29:51,923 --> 01:29:53,253
(My vacation)

2236
01:29:53,623 --> 01:29:55,492
(The siblings are finally kicking off their vacation.)

2237
01:29:55,493 --> 01:29:56,693
(All that's missing here...)

2238
01:29:57,463 --> 01:29:59,192
(is kimchi to make it perfect.)

2239
01:29:59,193 --> 01:30:00,193
(That's right.)

2240
01:30:01,093 --> 01:30:02,933
(Then hand me the napa cabbage.)

2241
01:30:03,333 --> 01:30:05,302
(You know what to do, right?)

2242
01:30:05,303 --> 01:30:07,602
(Load me up.)

2243
01:30:07,603 --> 01:30:10,742
(Wherever they may be, )

2244
01:30:10,743 --> 01:30:12,703
(the siblings...)

2245
01:30:12,873 --> 01:30:13,873
(can instantly bring out...)

2246
01:30:13,874 --> 01:30:16,212
(the flavors of Korea.)

2247
01:30:16,213 --> 01:30:17,842
(Adding red chili powder...)

2248
01:30:17,843 --> 01:30:19,783
(spreads the aroma of Korean flavors.)

2249
01:30:20,413 --> 01:30:25,483
(Crab meat fried rice with alimango, a Filipino delicacy)

2250
01:30:26,923 --> 01:30:29,522
(The siblings were too happily immersed in...)

2251
01:30:29,523 --> 01:30:32,093
(their vacation to realize...)

2252
01:30:33,263 --> 01:30:34,792
(what it means to have...)

2253
01:30:34,793 --> 01:30:38,563
("labor" missing from their schedule.)

2254
01:30:39,363 --> 01:30:43,743
(In shock)

2255
01:30:45,303 --> 01:30:50,043
(Horrified)

2256
01:30:51,483 --> 01:30:57,083
(What is the true nature of the shocking "Dances with Turtles?")
